%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Parisians%20resist%20car-free%20zone%20around%20Eiffel%20Tower%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707574411000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107586590%2Cimgsize-80318.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fparis-mayors-car-free-eiffel-tower-zone-faces-resistance-from-police-chief-and-locals%2Farticleshow%2F107585449.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20Last%20Day%20in%20Parliament%20BJP%20Tries%20to%20Draw%20Ram%20Temple%20Back%20on%20Political%20Centre-Stage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20to%20parliament%20on%20Saturday%20(February%2010)%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20the%20Ram%20Janambhoomi%20showed%20India%E2%80%99s%20secularism%20to%20the%20world%20and%20that%20in%20no%20other%20country%20did%20the%20majority%20community%20have%20to%20fight%20such%20a%20long%20legal%20battle%20for%20its%20faith.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAddressing%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20during%20the%20discussion%20titled%20%E2%80%9CDiscussion%20on%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20historic%20Ram%20Temple%20and%20the%20Pran%20Pratishtha%E2%80%9D%2C%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20had%20showed%20to%20the%20country%20that%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20fulfil%20the%20promises%20they%20make.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20itself%20has%20given%20an%20order%20through%20a%205-judge%20bench%2C%20how%20can%20you%20question%20it%3F%20If%20you%20like%20the%20order%20then%20accept%20the%20order%20and%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20the%20order%20you%20still%20will%20have%20to%20respect%20the%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Supreme%20Court%20order%20has%20shown%20to%20the%20world%20India%E2%80%99s%20secular%20character.%20In%20no%20other%20country%20in%20the%20world%20did%20the%20majority%20community%20have%20to%20fight%20such%20a%20long%20legal%20battle%20for%20its%20faith.%20We%20have%20seen%20the%20way%2C%20and%20we%20have%20fought%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20only%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20judgement%20has%20a%20Ram%20Mandir%20been%20built.%20I%20want%20to%20reiterate%2C%20when%20everyone%20is%20celebrating%2C%20you%20should%20also%20welcome%20it%20and%20this%20is%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20nation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shah%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20said%20that%20January%2022%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20a%20long%20struggle%20since%201528%20that%20has%20ended%20with%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20date%20of%20January%2022%20marks%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20journey%20of%20great%20India.%20This%20day%20paves%20the%20way%20for%20Maa%20Bharti%20(mother%20India)%20to%20take%20us%20on%20the%20path%20of%20becoming%20Vishwaguru%20(world%20leader).%20It%20was%20a%20day%20that%20marked%20the%20hopes%2C%20aspirations%20and%20accomplishments%20of%20crores%20of%20devotees%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20mentioned%20it%20in%20our%20manifesto%2C%20they%20said%20it%20was%20only%20to%20win%20the%20elections%20and%20that%20the%20BJP%20keeps%20making%20promises%20like%20scrapping%20Article%20370%2C%20Ram%20Janmabhoomi%2C%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20or%20Triple%20Talaq.%20However%2C%20they%20oppose%20us%20every%20time%20we%20fulfil%20our%20promises.%20The%20temple%20shows%20that%20the%20BJP%20and%20PM%20Modi%20fulfill%20all%20their%20promises%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShah%20said%20that%20during%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%2C%20no%20political%20slogans%20were%20raised%20and%20the%20message%20was%20one%20of%20unity.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20say%20with%20folded%20hands%20that%20accept%20the%20message%20of%20unity%20and%20move%20forward%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20interim%20budget%20session%20of%20parliament%20which%20began%20on%20January%2031%20was%20due%20to%20end%20on%20February%209%20but%20was%20extended%20by%20a%20day%20to%20Saturday%2C%20with%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament%20holding%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20last%20month.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20the%20discussion%20Congress%20MP%20Gaurav%20Gogoi%20said%20that%20the%20party%20believes%20in%20secularism%20and%20that%20the%20treasury%20benches%20should%20leave%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20path%20of%20Nathuram%20Godse%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20believe%20in%20secularism%2C%20but%20not%20the%20western%20definition%20of%20secularism.%20India%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3Edharmik%20%3C%2Fem%3E(religious)%20country%20and%20we%20believe%20in%20sarva%20dharma%20sam%20bhava.%20We%20want%20to%20bind%20everyone.%20This%20is%20our%20culture%20and%20civilisation.%20I%20call%20upon%20the%20treasury%20benches%20to%20leave%20the%20path%20of%20Nathuram%20Godse%3B%20to%20not%20celebrate%20but%20condemn%20him.%20Ravana%20was%20killed%20by%20his%20arrogance.%20Your%20arrogance%20makes%20you%20blind%20to%20inflation%2C%20and%20problems%20in%20society%20%E2%80%93%20be%20it%20in%20Manipur%20or%20those%20faced%20by%20minorities.%20India%20is%20an%20ancient%20country%3B%20it%20was%20not%20born%20in%202014%20or%20on%20January%2022%2C%202024.%20Ram%20Lalla%20was%20always%20with%20us.%20Ram%20will%20be%20there%20when%20you%20lose%20too.%20Ram%20is%20in%20our%20hearts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gogoi%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGogoi%20also%20asked%20the%20treasury%20benches%20about%20why%20hatred%20has%20been%20infused%20to%20chants%20like%20%E2%80%9CJai%20Shree%20Ram.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20there%20such%20bitterness%2C%20and%20hatred%20when%20they%20say%20Jai%20Shri%20Ram%3F%20If%20you%20hate%20people%20and%20spread%20hatred%2C%20and%20disturb%20others%E2%80%99%20religious%20practices%2C%20you%20cannot%20be%20a%20Ram%20Bhakt%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20India%20Majlis-e-Ittehadul%20Muslimeen%20(AIMIM)%20MP%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20said%20that%20the%20government%20should%20clarify%20whether%20it%20believes%20in%20one%20religion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20ask%20if%20the%20Modi%20government%20is%20the%20government%20of%20a%20particular%20community%2C%20religion%20or%20the%20government%20of%20the%20entire%20country%3F%20Does%20the%20government%20of%20India%20have%20a%20religion%3F%20I%20believe%20that%20this%20country%20does%20not%20have%20a%20religion.%20Through%2022nd%20January%2C%20does%20this%20government%20want%20to%20give%20a%20message%20that%20one%20religion%20triumphed%20over%20the%20other%3F%20Does%20law%20allow%20this%3F%20What%20message%20do%20you%20give%20to%20the%2017%20crore%20Muslims%20in%20the%20country%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmol%20Ramsingh%20Kolhe%20of%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20(NCP)%20said%20that%20while%20the%20construction%20of%20Ram%20temple%20was%20historic%2C%20there%20should%20be%20%E2%80%9Cno%20politics%20over%20religion%20and%20religion%20should%20not%20be%20in%20politics.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20world%E2%80%99s%20history%20shows%20that%20religious%20fundamentalism%20is%20harmful%20while%20religious%20openness%20is%20constructive%20and%20that%20is%20what%20Hinduism%20shows%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Shiv%20Sena%20MP%20Priyanka%20Chaturvedi%20said%20crediting%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20to%20only%20Modi%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cinsult%20those%20who%20fought%20for%20500%20years%20including%20those%20who%20fought%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707573276000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F11121926%2FScreenshot-2024-01-11-at-12.18.29-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fon-last-day-in-parliament-bjp-tries-to-draw-ram-temple-back-on-political-centre-stage%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amit%20Shah%2C%20who%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20pran%20pratishthan%20ceremony%2C%20spoke%20of%20the%20Ayodhya%20litigation%20in%20court.%20Congress'%20Gaurav%20Gogoi%20asked%20BJP%20to%20shed%20the%20%26quot%3Bpath%20of%20Nathuram%20Godse%26quot%3B%20and%20AIMIM's%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%20asked%20if%20the%20government%20only%20favoured%20one%20particular%20faith.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fon-last-day-in-parliament-bjp-tries-to-draw-ram-temple-back-on-political-centre-stage%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Peace%20Negotiations%20Between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20Failed%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20Ukrainian%20war%20approaches%20its%20second%20anniversary%2C%20there%20is%20renewed%2C%20if%20rather%20limp%2C%20talk%20of%20a%20ceasefire%20followed%20by%20negotiations.%20The%20premise%20(and%20promise)%20is%20that%20since%20neither%20side%20can%20%E2%80%98win%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20makes%20sense%20to%20start%20making%20peace.%20Few%20now%20remember%20that%20the%20war%20almost%20ended%20before%20it%20got%20going.%20On%20February%2024%2C%202022%2C%20Russia%20launched%20ground%20and%20air%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine%20on%20four%20fronts.%20On%20February%2028%2C%202022%2C%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20officials%20came%20together%20in%20Gomel%2C%20Belarus%20to%20start%20negotiating%20peace.%20Peace%20talks%20continued%20on%20and%20off%20for%20a%20month%20before%20being%20called%20off.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKnowledge%20of%20these%20talks%20has%20been%20steadily%20leaking%20out%20ever%20since%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20waved%20a%20%E2%80%98peace%20agreement%E2%80%99%20before%20Russian%20TV%20cameras%20on%20June%2017%2C%202023%2C%20which%2C%20he%20said%2C%20Ukraine%20had%20%E2%80%98trashed%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9CTreaty%20on%20permanent%20neutrality%20and%20security%20guarantees%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D%20with%2018%20articles%20and%20an%20appendix%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%98armed%20forces%20and%20other%20things%E2%80%99%20Putin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20month%2C%20Kremlin%20spokesperson%20Dmitri%20Peskov%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CBritain%20had%20sunk%20chances%20of%20a%20peace%20deal%20in%202022%20by%20putting%20pressure%20of%20Kyiv%20to%20refuse%20a%20draft%20deal%E2%80%9D%20shortly%20after%20Russia%20sent%20troops%20into%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20actually%20happened%20in%20February-March%202022%3F%20And%20what%20does%20it%20tell%20us%20about%20the%20prospects%20of%20peace%20today%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20negotiations%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20invaded%20Ukraine%20on%20February%2024%2C%202022%3B%20four%20days%20later%2C%20both%20sides%20started%20talking%20in%20Belarus.%20According%20to%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F12%2F28%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fukraine-russia-peace-talks.html%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cb%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cspan%3EUkraine%20demanded%20Russia%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20war%20atrocities%2C%20withdraw%20from%20all%20captured%20Ukraine%20territory%2C%20including%20Crimea%2C%20and%20pay%20reparations.%20Russia%20demanded%20Ukrainian%20recognition%20of%20its%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20in%202014%2C%20permanent%20Ukrainian%20neutrality%2C%20and%20autonomy%20for%20the%20ethnic%20Russian%20provinces%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eoblasts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20eastern%20and%20south-eastern%20Ukraine.%20No%20progress%20was%20made%2C%20but%20both%20sides%20agreed%20to%20continue%20talking%2C%20this%20time%20with%20representatives%20of%20their%20foreign%20and%20defence%20ministries%2C%20and%20presidential%20administrations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20a%20short%20postponement%2C%20talks%20restarted%20in%20the%20Brest%20region%20of%20Belarus%20on%20March%203.%20The%20discussions%20concentrated%20on%20establishing%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2022%2F03%2F03%2Frussia-ukraine-peace-talks-belarus%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehumanitarian%20corridors%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20for%20Ukrainian%20refugees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%20talks%20on%20March%207%20reverted%20to%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20requirements%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20fighting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fkremlin-says-russian-military-action-will-stop-moment-if-ukraine-meets-2022-03-07%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EReuters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%20Kremlin%20spokesman%20Peskov%20saying%20that%20Russia%20would%20stop%20its%20operations%20%E2%80%98in%20a%20moment%E2%80%99%20if%20Ukraine%20enshrined%20neutrality%20in%20its%20constitution%2C%20and%20accepted%20the%20loss%20of%20Crimea%20and%20the%20breakaway%20regions%20of%20Donbas.%20The%20Ukrainians%20stood%20by%20their%20previous%20demand%20for%20a%20complete%20Russian%20withdrawal%20from%20all%20occupied%20territories%2C%20including%20Crimea%2C%20plus%20reparations.%20Despite%20complications%20over%20humanitarian%20corridors%2C%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPodolyak_M%2Fstatus%2F1500891711450583041%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Efirst%20three%20rounds%20showed%20some%20progress%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Kyiv%20said%20it%20was%20willing%20to%20consider%20a%20key%20Moscow%20demand%2C%20guaranteed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2022%2F03%2F07%2Frussia-ukraine-peace-talks-third-round-makes-little-progress%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eneutrality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ukrainians%20had%20never%20liked%20the%20negotiations%20being%20held%20in%20Belarus.%20Turkey%E2%80%99s%20prime%20minister%20Reep%20Erdogan%20was%20eager%20to%20broker%20a%20peace%20deal%2C%20and%20so%2C%20on%20March%2010%2C%20there%20was%20a%20switch%20of%20venue%20to%20the%20seaside%20resort%20of%20Antalya%20in%20Turkey%2C%20with%20the%20Antalya%20Diplomacy%20Forum%20providing%20an%20opportunity%20for%20the%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20foreign%20ministers%20Sergey%20Lavrov%20and%20Dmytro%20Kuleba%20to%20meet%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20war%20started.%20They%20discussed%20temporary%20ceasefire%20agreements%20in%20heavily%20embattled%20regions%2C%20especially%20Mariopul%2C%20to%20allow%20for%20humanitarian%20corridors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20one%20and%20a%20half%20hour%20meeting%20chaired%20by%20the%20Turkish%20foreign%20minister%20Mevlut%20Cavusogiu%20failed%20to%20produce%20any%20breakthrough%20even%20on%20this%20limited%20issue.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20foreign%20minister%20%E2%80%9Cunfortunately%20Minister%20Lavrov%20was%20not%20in%20a%20position%20to%20commit%20himself%20to%20anything%E2%80%99%20without%20reference%20back%20to%20Putin.%20The%20official%20website%20of%20the%20Russian%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20told%20a%20different%20story%3A%20the%20Ukrainian%20side%20was%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Creplace%20or%20devalue%20the%20existing%20negotiations%20track%2C%20which%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20Belarus%E2%80%9D%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20Turkish%20Foreign%20Minister%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20an%20important%20start%20as%20the%20foreign%20ministers%20of%20both%20sides%20were%20present.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBetween%20March%2014-17%2C%20a%20fifth%20round%20of%20peace%20talks%20took%20place%20via%20video%20conference.%20This%20produced%20the%20best%20outcome%20so%20far.%20On%20March%2015%2C%20Ukrainian%20President%20Zelensky%20reported%20%E2%80%98real%20progress%E2%80%99%3B%20next%20day%20Lavrov%20spoke%20of%20%E2%80%98some%20hope%20for%20reaching%20a%20compromise%E2%80%99.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F7b341e46-d375-4817-be67-802b7fa77ef1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20March%2016%20signalled%20a%2015-point%20draft%20deal%20by%20which%20Kyiv%20gave%20up%20its%20NATO%20ambitions%20in%20return%20for%20security%20guarantees%20outside%20NATO.%20In%20an%20interview%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabcnews.go.com%2FInternational%2Fukraines-lead-negotiator-talks-russia-months%2Fstory%3Fid%3D83626948%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EABC%20news%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%2C%20Ukrainian%20negotiator%20Podolyak%20said%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20demands%20and%20position%20have%20%E2%80%9Csoftened%20significantly%E2%80%9D%20and%20%3Atherefore%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2022%2F03%2F16%2Fpeace-talks-russia-ukraine-lavrov-zelensky%2F%5C%22%3Ewe%20have%20much%20confidence%20that%20we%20will%20have%20a%20cease-fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20coming%20days%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0He%20attributed%20the%20softening%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20Russian%20%E2%80%98blitzkrieg%E2%80%99%20to%20capture%20any%20big%20cities%2C%20leaving%20it%20with%20%E2%80%98no%20chances%20whatsoever%20to%20move%20further%20into%20Ukraine%20territory%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20this%20time%2C%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20peace%20momentum%20had%20replaced%20war%20momentum.%20There%20was%20no%20breakthrough%20at%20the%20sixth%20round%20of%20negotiations%20on%20March%2021.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Frussian%2Fnews-60822040%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBBC%20news%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vesty.co.il%2Fmain%2Farticle%2FK9YQD1XMC%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVedomosti%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(%20Russian%20newspaper)%20President%20Zelensky%20requested%20a%20face-to-face%20meeting%20with%20Putin.%20Lavrov%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputin-zelenskiy-meeting-needed-once-sides-closer-key-issues-russias-lavrov-2022-03-28%2F%5C%22%3Erejected%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20and%20said%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9C%20It%20should%20happen%20once%20the%20two%20sides%20are%20closer%20to%20agreeing%20on%20key%20issues%E2%80%9D.%20This%20rebuff%20brought%20a%20temporary%20halt%20to%20the%20sequence%20of%20negotiations.%20It%20also%20coincided%20with%20the%20start%20of%20a%20Ukrainian%20counter-offensive%20on%20March%2022%2C%20which%2C%20by%20April%203%2C%20had%20ended%20Russian%20threat%20to%20Kyiv.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0The%20seventh%20round%20of%20talks%20on%20March%2029%20saw%20the%20renewal%20of%20face-to-face%20negotiations%20in%20Istanbul.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurointegration.com.ua%2Feng%2Farticles%2F2022%2F03%2F30%2F7136915%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EEuropean%20Pravda%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%20that%20this%20had%20so%20far%20been%20the%20%E2%80%98most%20effective%20round%20of%20Ukraine-Russian%20negotiations%E2%80%99.%20The%20discussion%20centred%20on%20a%20draft%20treaty%2C%20the%20gist%20of%20which%20was%20permanent%20Ukrainian%20neutrality%20and%20non-nuclear%20status%2C%20in%20return%20for%20which%20Ukraine%20would%20have%20security%20guarantees%20similar%20to%20Article%205%20of%20the%20NATO%20military%20alliance%20from%20China%2C%20Russia%2C%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20Belarus%20and%20others.%20Ukraine%20would%20also%20start%20a%2015-year%20consultation%20period%20on%20the%20status%20of%20Crimea%2C%20though%20reserving%20the%20right%20to%20reconquer%20Luhansk%20and%20Donetsk%20(Ukrainian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2023%2F06%2F14%2F7406819%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPravda%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20For%20its%20part%2C%20Russia%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2022%2F03%2F29%2Fukraine-russia-turkey-negotiations%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cdrastically%20reduce%E2%80%9D%20military%20activity%3C%2Fa%3E%20near%20Kyiv%20to%20%E2%80%98create%20the%20necessary%20conditions%20for%20further%20negotiations%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EUkraine%E2%80%99s%20successful%20counter-offensive%20had%20started%20a%20week%20before%20the%20Istanbul%20peace%20talks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20Russian%20offer%20to%20%E2%80%98withdraw%E2%80%99%20on%20March%2029%20was%20thus%20far%20from%20voluntary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20draft%20was%20the%20one%20Putin%20waved%20on%20television%20on%20June%2017%2C%202023.%20He%20called%20it%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.ru%2Fpolitika%2F17997587%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cnot%20bad%20result%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20talks%20of%20March%2029%20ended%20in%20the%20expectation%20that%20the%20draft%20agreement%20would%20be%20initialled%20by%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20principals%2C%20laying%20the%20foundations%20for%20a%20compromise%20peace.%20Putin%20even%20suggested%20meeting%20Zelensky.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20never%20happened%2C%20and%20that%20was%20the%20end%20of%20the%20bilateral%20talks.%20Russian%20foreign%20minister%20Sergey%20Lavrov%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussia-says-talks-with-ukraine-are-not-going-in-any-form-ifax-2022-05-17%2F%5C%22%3Estated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9C%20Washington%2C%20London%20and%20Brussels%20want%20to%20use%20Ukraine%20to%20their%20advantage%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cno%20peace%20deal%20can%20be%20made%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EZelensky%20stated%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20not%20agree%20to%20peace%20until%20Russia%20agreed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2022%2F05%2F25%2Fukraine-russia-invasion-live-updates%2F9916925002%2F%5C%22%3Ereturn%20Crimea%20and%20Donbas%20region%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20sum%20up%3A%20in%20the%20early%20weeks%20that%20followed%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20two%20engaged%20in%20substantial%20attempts%20to%20negotiate%20a%20peace%20settlement.%20These%20could%20have%20ended%20the%20war%20before%20the%20devastation%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20infrastructure%2C%20the%20massive%20loss%20of%20lives%2C%20and%20the%20increased%20risk%20of%20unchecked%20escalation.%20They%20featured%20an%20offer%20by%20Ukraine%20not%20to%20join%20NATO%20in%20return%20for%20equivalent%20security%20guarantees.%20Crucial%20points%20of%20disagreement%20about%20Crimea%20and%20Donbas%2C%20as%20well%20as%20about%20the%20practicability%20of%20the%20non-Nato%20guarantees%2C%20remained.%20But%20on%20March%2029%2C%20both%20sides%20apparently%20expected%20to%20go%20on%20talking.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EReasons%20for%20Failure%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWas%20there%20a%20real%20chance%20for%20peace%20in%20March%202022%3F%20If%20so%2C%20why%20was%20it%20lost%3F%20Let%E2%80%99s%20take%20these%20questions%20in%20turn.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20sides%20were%20never%20as%20close%20to%20each%20other%20as%20the%20formulae%20they%20concocted%20suggested.%20Yes%2C%20Ukraine%20was%20willing%20to%20renounce%20joining%20NATO%2C%20but%20knew%20that%20equivalent%20security%20guarantees%20by%20the%20great%20powers%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20come%20by.%20Nor%20was%20there%20any%20real%20prospect%20of%20Russia%20%E2%80%98negotiating%20away%E2%80%99%20its%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20in%202014.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20as%20far%20as%20known%2C%20no%20progress%20had%20been%20made%20in%20settling%20the%20future%20of%20the%20Donbas-the%20Russian-speaking%20provinces%20of%20eastern%20and%20south-eastern%20Ukraine.%20Agreements%20between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20brokered%20by%20France%20and%20Germany%2C%20known%20as%20Minsk%20I%20and%20Minsk%20II%20intended%20to%20give%20the%20provinces%20a%20degree%20of%20autonomy%20within%20Ukraine%20had%20collapsed%20in%202015.%20Now%20they%20were%20partly%20occupied%20by%20Russian%20troops.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EImportant%20in%20determining%20the%20immediate%20outcome%20were%20the%20fortunes%20of%20war.%20It%20was%20their%20initial%20failure%20to%20capture%20Kyiv%20which%20got%20the%20Russians%20talking%3B%20their%20continuing%20offensive%20in%20March%20which%20brought%20Ukraine%20to%20the%20table.%20With%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20counter-offensive%20of%20March%2022%2C%20the%20Russians%20had%20a%20renewed%20incentive%20to%20negotiate%2C%20while%20Ukraine%20was%20starting%20to%20scent%20victory.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Ukrainian%20counter-attack%20also%20crucially%20strengthened%20the%20western%20resolve%20to%20support%20Ukraine%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20withdrawal%20by%20Ukraine%20of%20even%20cosmetic%20concessions.%20As%20the%20Ukrainian%20army%20continued%20to%20inflict%20defeats%20on%20the%20Russians%2C%20and%20western%20military%20aid%20was%20ramped%20up%20in%20the%20summer%202022%2C%20Ukraine%20had%20little%20further%20reason%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20Russians.%20The%20damage%20inflicted%20by%20continued%20fighting%20would%20be%20paid%20back%20by%20victory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20structural%20obstacles%20to%20successful%20peace%20negotiations.%20However%2C%20there%20were%20also%20two%20dramatic%20events%20which%20tilted%20the%20balance%20against%20peace.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Russian%20forces%20were%20driven%20out%20of%20the%20Kyiv%20region%20at%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20Ukrainians%20claimed%20to%20have%20discovered%20evidence%20of%20atrocities%20%E2%80%93%20rapes%2C%20murders%2C%20massacres%2C%20looting%2C%20indiscriminate%20bombings%20and%20other%20war%20crimes%20%E2%80%93%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Farticles%2F2022%2F05%2F5%2F7344096%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBucha%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flife.pravda.com.ua%2Fsociety%2F2022%2F04%2F6%2F248117%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIrpin%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Farticles%2F2022%2F04%2F9%2F7338269%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBorodianka%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pravda.com.ua%2Feng%2Fnews%2F2022%2F05%2F4%2F7343968%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAzovstal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20These%20atrocious%20events%2C%20Russian%20responsibility%20for%20which%20has%20been%20confirmed%20by%20the%20UN%20High%20Commission%20on%20Human%20Rights%2C%20gave%20Ukraine%20an%20additional%20reason%20to%20break%20off%20negotiations%2C%20one%20strongly%20supported%20by%20the%20West.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAn%20even%20bigger%20obstacle%20to%20further%20talks%20may%20have%20been%20the%20arrival%20in%20Kyiv%2C%20on%20April%206%2C%20of%20British%20Prime%20Minister%20Boris%20Johnson%20%E2%80%9CJohnson%20brought%20two%20simple%20messages%20to%20Kyiv.%20The%20first%20is%20that%20Putin%20is%20a%20war%20criminal%3B%20he%20should%20be%20pressured%2C%20not%20negotiated%20with.%20And%20the%20second%20is%20that%20even%20if%20Ukraine%20is%20ready%20to%20sign%20some%20agreements%20on%20guarantees%20with%20Putin%2C%20they%20%5Bthe%20NATO%20powers%5D%20are%20not%E2%80%9D.%20is%20how%20one%20of%20Zelenskyy%E2%80%99s%20negotiators%20associates%2C%20Savyd%20Arakmahia%2C%20summed%20up%20the%20gist%20of%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20remarks.%20Three%20days%20after%20Johnson%20returned%20home%20Putin%20announced%20publicly%20that%20talks%20with%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%9Chad%20reached%20a%20dead%20end%E2%80%9D.%20For%20his%20part%20Johnson%20promised%20Zelensky%20%24130m%20of%20military%20equipment%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F04%2F09%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fboris-johnson-kyiv-ukraine-aid.html%5C%22%3E%24500m%20in%20in%20financial%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20while%20President%20Biden%20announced%20a%20%24%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defense.gov%2FNews%2FNews-Stories%2FArticle%2FArticle%2F3006622%2Fpresident-biden-announces-new-800m-in-military-assistance-to-ukraine%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E800m%20military%20package%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJohnson%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20has%20been%20discounted%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20he%20was%20in%20no%20position%20to%20tell%20the%20Ukrainian%20government%20what%20to%20do.%20This%20is%20legally%20correct%2C%20but%20vacuous.%20He%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20position%20to%20tell%20them%20whether%20NATO%20powers%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20join%20Russia%20in%20guaranteeing%20Ukrainian%20independence%20outside%20NATO%2C%20and%20under%20what%20conditions%20Britain%20(and%20the%20USA)%20would%20supply%20further%20military%20and%20economic%20aid.%20Had%20Johnson%E2%80%99s%20promise%20of%20support%20been%20conditional%20rather%20than%20unconditional%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2022%2F09%2F22%2Fputin-ukraine-threats-biden-cuban-missile-crisis%2F%5C%22%3Eit%20is%20inconceivable%20that%20negotiations%20would%20not%20have%20continued.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20of%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20military%20situation%20in%20Ukraine%20now%20in%20stalemate%2C%20there%20is%20predictable%20new%20pressure%20for%20peace%20talks.%20There%20have%20been%20reports%20of%20%E2%80%98secret%20talks%E2%80%99%20between%20US%20and%20Russian%20officials.%20There%20have%20been%20public%20peace%20initiatives%20by%20China%2C%20the%20Vatican%2C%20Brazil%2C%20Mexico%20and%20others.%20Thought%20leaders%20like%20Anatol%20Lieven%20and%20Jeffrey%20Sachs%20have%20strongly%20argued%20for%20an%20immediate%20ceasefire.%20These%20initiatives%20seem%20to%20be%20based%20on%20a%20sense%20that%20the%20war%20is%20going%20nowhere%2C%20but%20that%20were%20it%20to%20go%20somewhere%2C%20it%20could%20easily%20escalate%20into%20a%20nuclear%20confrontation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Sergei%20Lavrov%20said%20that%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20%E2%80%98is%20not%20as%20much%20about%20Ukraine%20as%20about%20the%20legal%20world%20order%E2%80%99%20he%20correctly%20pinpointed%20the%20main%20obstacle%20to%20the%20restoration%20of%20peace%3A%20the%20lack%20of%20agreement%20between%20the%20great%20powers%20on%20a%20legitimate%20world%20order.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20it%20had%20a%20right%20and%20indeed%20a%20duty%20to%20intervene%20in%20Ukraine%20to%20protect%20its%20integrity%20and%20security%20runs%20up%20against%20the%20doctrine%20that%20legally%20established%20frontiers%20must%20not%20be%20changed%20by%20force.%20However%2C%20existing%20frontiers%2C%20often%20the%20result%20of%20inventive%20colonial-era%20map-making%2C%20may%20not%20accord%20with%20current%20realities.%20How%2C%20then%2C%20to%20change%20frontiers%20peacefully%20if%20sentiment%20or%20security%20demand%20it%3F%20Clearly%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20idea%20of%20Ukraine%20as%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20itself%20was%20incompatible%20with%20Ukrainian%20nationalism.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20claim%2C%20backed%20by%20the%20West%2C%20to%20total%20sovereignty%20in%20foreign%20policy%2C%20is%20incompatible%20with%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20historical%20conception%20of%20its%20security%20needs.%20The%20disparity%20between%20these%20two%20mental%20fabrics%20is%20the%20biggest%20structural%20obstacle%20to%20peace.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20breakdown%20of%20the%20peace%20talks%20in%20April%202022%2C%20the%20military%20situation%20has%20scarcely%20changed%3A%20Russia%20is%20no%20nearer%20defeating%20a%20Ukraine%20supplied%20by%20NATO%2C%20and%20Ukraine%20is%20no%20nearer%20defeating%20its%20stronger%20neighbour.%20Time%20is%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Russia%20with%20its%20far%20greater%20resources%20of%20manpower%2C%20artillery%2C%20and%20airpower.%20In%20these%20circumstances%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20strong%20temptation%20on%20the%20Ukrainian%2FNATO%20side%20to%20break%20the%20stalemate%20by%20scaling%20up%20the%20warfare.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20danger%20of%20escalation%20should%20certainly%20not%20be%20discounted.%20Nor%20have%20economic%20sanctions%20decisively%20affected%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20continue%20the%20war.%20The%20military%20stalemate%20prevents%20not%20just%20the%20resumption%20of%20%E2%80%98normality%E2%80%99%20within%20Ukraine%20and%20in%20Ukraine-Russian%20relations%20but%20stability%20in%20the%20world%20as%20a%20whole%2C%20unless%20we%20are%20willing%20to%20accept%20as%20%E2%80%98normal%E2%80%99%20the%20permanent%20division%20of%20the%20world%20into%20two%20antagonistic%20military%20and%20economic%20blocs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorians%20will%20naturally%20look%20to%20history%20for%20precedents%20and%20lessons.%20Ukraine%20has%20fought%20for%20its%20independence%20and%20won%2C%20much%20as%20Finland%20did%20in%201939-40.Admittedly%2C%20Finland%E2%80%99s%20independence%20came%20at%20the%20price%20of%20some%20territory.%20If%20we%20could%20think%20of%20the%20current%20Ukrainian%20achievement%20as%20a%20successful%20war%20of%20independence%2C%20we%20would%20be%20much%20less%20fixated%20on%20defining%20Ukrainian%20victory%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20reconquest%20of%20every%20bit%20of%20the%20map%20called%20Ukraine%20in%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%98security%20guarantees%E2%80%99%20for%20Ukraine%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eoutside%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20NATO%20in%20the%20Ukraine-Russian%20conversations%20of%20February-March%202022%20was%20groping%20towards%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20new%20security%20architecture%20to%20replace%20the%20NATO-Warsaw%20Pact%20system%20of%20the%20Cold%20War.%20Russia%20was%20demanding%20protection%20against%20NATO%3A%20Ukraine%20was%20seeking%20protection%20against%20Russia%20inside%20NATO.%20The%20compromise%20is%20a%20security%20structure%20of%20which%20NATO%20is%20a%20major%20but%20not%20the%20only%20part.%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20security%20should%20no%20more%20hinge%20on%20NATO%20membership%20than%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20on%20preventing%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20membership%20of%20NATO.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBill%20Burns%2C%20now%20director%20of%20the%20CIA%2C%20wrote%20in%201995%20that%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20a%20security%20order%20in%20Europe%20%E2%80%98sufficiently%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20interests%20so%20that%20a%20revived%20Russia%20will%20have%20no%20compelling%20reason%20to%20revise%20it%E2%80%99.%20Instead%20NATO%20enlargement%2C%20he%20later%20wrote%2C%20had%20left%20%E2%80%9Ca%20mark%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20relations%20with%20the%20West%20that%20would%20linger%20for%20decades%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20European%20(and%20indeed%20the%20global)%20security%20architecture%20should%20be%20one%20of%20%E2%80%98variable%20geometry%E2%80%99%2C%20with%20different%20structures%20of%20security%20provision%20available%20for%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%20but%20with%20the%20whole%20tending%20to%20war%20prevention.%20A%20reformed%20Security%20Council%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20should%20be%20the%20foundation%20(or%20arch)%20of%20any%20such%20design.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENone%20of%20this%20will%20come%20to%20pass%20by%20thought%20alone.%20So%20we%20must%20rely%20on%20new%20(and%20possibly%20tragic)%20facts%20on%20the%20ground%20to%20provide%20the%20impetus%20to%20action.%20But%20when%20the%20facts%20allow%20it%2C%20thought%20should%20be%20ready%20to%20take%20advantage.%20That%20is%20why%20one%20should%20continuously%20talk%20up%20the%20need%20and%20advantages%20for%20peace%20today%2C%20even%20if%20its%20time%20is%20not%20yet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERobert%20Skidelsky%20is%20an%20economic%20historian%20and%20author%20of%20a%20three-volume%20award-winning%20biography%20of%20the%20economist%2C%20John%20Maynard%20Keynes.%20He%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707572366000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-peace-negotiations-between-russia-and-ukraine-failed%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20Ukrainian%20war%20approaches%20its%20second%20anniversary%2C%20there%20is%20renewed%2C%20if%20rather%20limp%2C%20talk%20of%20a%20ceasefire%20followed%20by%20negotiations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhy-peace-negotiations-between-russia-and-ukraine-failed%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Travelling%20Under%20the%20Shadow%20of%20Saffron%20Flags%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09184841%2FUntitled-design-8-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20Patna%20in%20Bihar%20to%20Jodhpur%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20spanning%20the%20vast%20expanse%20of%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%2C%20one%20can%20witness%20a%20spectrum%20of%20sights%3A%20from%20humble%20huts%20and%20sturdy%20concrete%20houses%20to%20upscale%20shops%20and%20bustling%20roadside%20eateries.%20Saffron%20flags%20bearing%20the%20inscription%20%E2%80%9CJai%20Shri%20Ram%E2%80%9D%20and%20images%20of%20Ram%20wielding%20his%20bow%20and%20arrow%20adorn%20rooftops%2C%20fluttering%20proudly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20train%20traverses%20through%20the%20Sultanpur%20district%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20Alwar%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20nearly%20800%20kilometres%20apart%2C%20a%20stark%20contrast%20unfolds.%20Beneath%20the%20waving%20flags%2C%20one%20encounters%20impoverished%20dwellings%2C%20ubiquitous%20fodder%20tubs%2C%20and%20cowherds%20guiding%20their%20cattle%20through%20fields%20of%20mustard%20and%20wheat.%20All%20pass%20by%20in%20a%20blur%20of%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20as%20the%20road%20progresses%20through%20Meerut%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20approaches%20Gurga