%20cynicism%20that%20had%20unfolded%20in%20Ayodhya%20demanded%20a%20response%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20from%20Karnad%20but%20also%20from%20his%20circle%20of%20friends%20and%20other%20artists.%20The%20Coalition%20for%20Secularism%2C%20a%20voluntary%20collective%2C%20came%20together%20in%20Bangalore%20to%20help%20people%20speak%20up%20and%20organise%20against%20this%20cult%20of%20violent%20and%20weaponised%20faith.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20forefront%20of%20artists%E2%80%99%20protests%20and%20solidarity%20was%20the%20Safdar%20Hashmi%20Memorial%20Trust%2C%20or%20SAHMAT.%20The%20Trust%20held%20events%20throughout%20the%20year%20of%201993%3B%20their%20climax%20took%20place%20in%20Ayodhya%20on%20Independence%20Day%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2015%2C%201993%2C%20several%20hundreds%20of%20artists%2C%20writers%2C%20scholars%20and%20organisers%20gathered%20in%20Ayodhya%20to%20reclaim%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20heritage%20from%20hatred.%20On%20the%20Ram-ki-Paidi%20ghat%20along%20the%20Sarayu%20River%2C%20they%20held%20an%20all-night%20performance%20of%20music%20and%20dance%2C%20Muktnaad.%20Legendary%20performers%20such%20as%20Sitara%20Devi%2C%20Kelucharan%20Mohapatra%2C%20Girija%20Devi%20and%20Capt.%20Lakshmi%20Sahgal%20came%20together%20in%20a%20spectacular%20display%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20heritage.%20Karnad%20was%20its%20master%20of%20ceremonies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10152953%2Funnamed-4.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10152953%2Funnamed-4.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10152953%2Funnamed-4-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10152953%2Funnamed-4-1024x678.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696514%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGirija%20Devi%2C%20Pt.%20Kishan%20Maharaj%2C%20Sita%20Devi%2C%20Umayalpuram%20Sivaramani%2C%20Swami%20Pagal%20Das%2C%20and%20Girish%20Karnad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20publication%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ETwenty%20Years%20of%20SAHMAT%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20recalls%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20the%20very%20fact%20of%20its%20being%20held%2C%20Muktnaad%20posed%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20forces%20of%20communalism%20who%20had%20sought%20to%20present%20Ayodhya%2C%20and%20the%20traditions%20associated%20with%20it%2C%20as%20their%20special%20preserve%2C%20and%20their%20siege%20of%20Ayodhya%20was%20broken.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20had%20turned%20now%20to%20confront%20the%20politics%20of%20religious%20division%20and%20resentment%2C%20and%20he%20would%20actively%20oppose%20it%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20engagement%20with%20violence%20in%20public%20and%20cultural%20spheres%20were%20refracted%20through%20his%20later%20plays%20like%20%3Cem%3ECrossing%20to%20Talikota%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20in%20less%20well-known%20writings%2C%20some%20published%20exclusively%20in%20Kannada.%20Among%20these%20are%20two%20short%20stories%20written%20by%20Karnad%20in%20the%201990s.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAlida%20Mele%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20takes%20its%20title%20from%20K.%20Shivarama%20Karanth%E2%80%99s%20famed%20novel.%20The%20story%20was%20published%20in%20the%201998%20Deepavali%20special%20issue%20of%20%3Cem%3EKannada%20Prabha%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAlida%20Mele%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20auto-fictional%20story%20where%20he%20is%20himself%20a%20character%20in%20conversation%20with%20Rizvi%2C%20an%20aspiring%20producer%20who%20wishes%20to%20adapt%20Karanth%E2%80%99s%20novel%20into%20a%20film.%20An%20English%20translation%20by%20Srinath%20Perur%20will%20be%20published%20in%20the%20new%20Bengaluru-based%20literary%20journal%2C%20South%20Parade%2C%20expected%20in%20April%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20also%20persisted%20in%20his%20activism%20against%20political%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20mushrooming%20of%20new%20provocations%20after%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition.%20One%20of%20these%2C%20close%20to%20home%2C%20was%20the%20dargah%20of%20Baba%20Budhangiri%20in%20the%20district%20of%20Chikkamagaluru%2C%20a%20place%20revered%20by%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus%20alike.%20In%202003%2C%20the%20dargah%20became%20the%20target%20of%20a%20Bajrang%20Dal%20campaign%20to%20create%20an%20%E2%80%9CAyodhya%20of%20the%20South%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20demanded%20new%20and%20exclusionary%20Brahminical%20rites%20at%20the%20shrine%20and%20called%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20tombs%20nearby%20to%20declare%20it%20as%20an%20exclusively%20Hindu%20religious%20site.%20In%20December%20that%20year%2C%20at%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20suggestion%2C%20he%20and%20a%20number%20of%20his%20writer%20friends%20went%20to%20Chikkamagaluru%20to%20understand%20what%20was%20happening%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5.jpg%20828w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10153153%2Funnamed-5-300x208.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696515%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22573%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ELeft%20to%20right%3A%20Dr%20K%20Marulasiddappa%2C%20Professor%20VS%20Sreedhara%2C%20the%20actor%20and%20writer%20GK%20Govinda%20Rao%2C%20Gauri%20Lankesh%2C%20Shudra%20Srinivas%2C%20and%20Girish%20Karnad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20those%20writers%20was%20the%20newspaper%20editor%20Gauri%20Lankesh.%20She%20was%20an%20unflinching%20critic%20of%20Hindutva%20extremism%20and%20ran%20the%20%3Cem%3EGauri%20Lankesh%20Patrike%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20Kannada%20weekly%20tabloid%20with%20a%20popular%20and%20non-metro%20readership%20across%20Karnataka.%20She%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3ELankesh%20Patrike%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202003%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20amazing%20things%20happened%20over%20the%20two%20weeks%20when%20we%20organised%20communal%20harmony%20meetings%20at%20Chikmagalur%20and%20Bababudangiri%2C%20and%20called%20upon%20people%20to%20stop%20Karnataka%20from%20becoming%20another%20Gujarat%20and%20Bababudangiri%20from%20being%20turned%20into%20Ayodhya%20by%20the%20saffron%20brigade%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20visit%20to%20the%20shrine%2C%20Karnad%2C%20Lankesh%20and%20their%20association%2C%20the%20Souharda%20Vedike%2C%20began%20to%20receive%20serious%20threats%20from%20right-wing%20extremist%20groups.%20They%20were%20undeterred%20in%20their%20plan%20to%20make%20a%20second%20trip.%20On%20the%20way%20there%2C%20%E2%80%9CGirish%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20were%20stopped%20midway%20and%20placed%20under%20detention%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20filmmaker%20KM%20Chaitanya%20recalled.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20Gauri%20was%20adventurous.%20She%20didn%E2%80%99t%20come%20with%20us.%20She%20somehow%20smuggled%20herself%20past%20the%20police%20and%20landed%20at%20Baba%20Budangiri.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%20in%202014%2C%20mob%20brutality%20against%20the%20poorest%20of%20Indian%20Muslims%20became%20frequent.%20Regular%20Indians%20came%20together%20to%20protest%20these%20lynchings.%20A%20major%20wave%20of%20civil%20pushback%20was%20the%20%E2%80%98Not%20In%20My%20Name%E2%80%99%20protests%20of%20June%202017.%20The%20event%20in%20Bengaluru%20was%20held%20on%20the%20steps%20of%20the%20Town%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%E2%80%99s%20friend%2C%20the%20historian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20recalled%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGirish%20Karnad%2C%20however%2C%20stayed%20well%20to%20the%20south%20of%20the%20Town%20Hall%E2%80%A6%20He%20was%20in%20his%20late%20seventies%2C%20and%20suffering%20from%20a%20degenerative%20respiratory%20disorder%2C%20which%20obliged%20him%20to%20carry%20a%20cylinder%20at%20all%20times%20which%20sent%20oxygen%20to%20his%20lungs%20through%20tubes%20stuck%20into%20his%20nose.%20I%20did%20not%20expect%20Karnad%20to%20come.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20began%20to%20rain.%20We%20carried%20on%20standing%2C%20in%20the%20open.%20A%20figure%20slipped%20in%20silently%20on%20my%20left.%20It%20was%20Girish.%20He%20had%20walked%20at%20least%20ten%20minutes%20in%20the%20rain%20from%20whichever%20side%20road%20his%20driver%20had%20parked%20his%20car%20in%2C%20carrying%20his%20cylinder%20and%20his%20tubes%20with%20him%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20Muslim%20men%2C%20in%20the%20row%20in%20front%20of%20us%2C%20murmured%20with%20delight%20and%20approval.%20One%20of%20them%20said%20to%20the%20other%2C%20in%20English%3A%20%E2%80%9CGirish%20Karnad%20Sir%20has%20arrived!%E2%80%9D%20That%20so%20many%20Hindus%20(and%20Christians)%20had%20come%20from%20all%20parts%20of%20the%20city%20mattered%20to%20them%3B%20that%20this%20particular%20Indian%20had%20come%20mattered%20most%20of%20all.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696519%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGirish%20Karnad%20at%20the%20protest%20with%20his%20wife%20Dr%20Saraswathy%20Ganapathy%20standing%20behind%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Not%20In%20My%20Name%20protest%20foreshadowed%20what%20would%20be%20one%20of%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20last%20public%20appearances.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20September%202017%2C%20Gauri%20Lankesh%20was%20assassinated%20by%20suspected%20right-wing%20extremists%20outside%20her%20home%20in%20Bengaluru.%20The%20following%20January%2C%20on%20Gauri%E2%80%99s%20first%20birthday%20after%20her%20assassination%2C%20an%20enormous%20gathering%20of%20citizens%20took%20place%20at%20the%20Town%20Hall.%20The%20memorial%20doubled%20as%20a%20protest%20in%20solidarity%20with%20other%2C%20recently%20jailed%20activists%2C%20who%20were%20being%20smeared%20in%20the%20media%20as%20%E2%80%98Urban%20Naxals%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKarnad%20arrived%20at%20the%20Town%20Hall%20again%2C%20wearing%20a%20cannula%20and%20carrying%20his%20oxygen%20machine.%20Around%20his%20neck%2C%20he%20wore%20a%20sign%20that%20announced%3A%20%E2%80%98Me%20Too%20Urban%20Naxal.%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%9CIf%20speaking%20up%20means%20being%20a%20Naxal%20then%20I%20am%20an%20Urban%20Naxal%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20there.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20proud%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20the%20hit%20list.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCynicism%20destroys%20our%20infinite%20capacity%20to%20improve%20our%20lot.%20Be%20positive%20and%20you%E2%80%99ll%20find%20your%20inner%20courage.%20I%20hold%20precious%20our%20pluralism%20and%20multiculturalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Girish%20Karnad%20in%20a%202004%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20published%20as%20the%20second%20edition%20of%20the%20weekly%20newsletter%2C%20The%20World%20of%20Girish%20Karnad.%20Subscribe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fworldofgirishkarnad.substack.com%2F%3Fr%3Dhzn2u%26utm_campaign%3Dsubscribe-page-share-screen%26utm_medium%3Dweb%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707561362000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155158%2Funnamed-6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-advanis-rath-yatra-compelled-girish-karnad-to-enter-politics%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20destruction%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20in%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20life.%20%E2%80%9CI%20never%20entered%20politics%20until%20Advani%20started%20his%20Rath%20Yatra%20to%20Ayodhya%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%201999%20interview.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fhow-advanis-rath-yatra-compelled-girish-karnad-to-enter-politics%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Iran's%20foreign%20minister%20affirms%20support%20for%20Hezbollah%20amid%20escalating%20tensions%20in%20the%20region%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707561102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107582515%2Cimgsize-137778.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-foreign-minister-affirms-support-for-hezbollah-amid-escalating-tensions-in-the-region%2Farticleshow%2F107581848.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107581848.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EIran's%20Foreign%20Minister%2C%20Hossein%20Amirabdollahian%2C%20expressed%20commitment%20to%20supporting%20Hezbollah%2C%20Hamas%2C%20and%20Islamic%20Jihad%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Beirut.%20He%20praised%20Hezbollah's%20role%20in%20the%20conflict%20and%20emphasized%20Lebanon's%20security%20as%20crucial%20for%20Iran.%20Amirabdollahian%20will%20meet%20Lebanese%20officials%20and%20Hezbollah%20leader%20Nasrallah.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-foreign-minister-affirms-support-for-hezbollah-amid-escalating-tensions-in-the-region%2Farticleshow%2F107581848.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-foreign-minister-affirms-support-for-hezbollah-amid-escalating-tensions-in-the-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F107581848.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firans-foreign-minister-affirms-support-for-hezbollah-amid-escalating-tensions-in-the-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F107581848.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Caste%20Census%20is%20Critical%20But%20Not%20Synonymous%20with%20Social%20Justice%3A%20Sociologist%20Satish%20Deshpande%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10155115%2FEffect-2024-02-10T155015.359.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20tool%2C%20a%20vitally%20necessary%20one%2C%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20social%20justice%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20a%20goal%20in%20itself%2C%20said%20eminent%20sociologist%20Satish%20Deshpande%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20delivering%20a%20lecture%20on%20the%20theme%20%E2%80%9CWill%20a%20%E2%80%98Caste%20Census%E2%80%99%20Deliver%20Social%20Justice%3F%2C%E2%80%9D%20organised%20by%20the%20Bengaluru%20Collective%20in%20association%20with%20the%20Law%20and%20Development%20Committee%20of%20the%20St.%20Joseph%E2%80%99s%20College%20of%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeshpande%2C%20currently%20M.%20N.%20Srinivas%20Chair%20Professor%20at%20the%20Institute%20for%20Social%20and%20Economic%20Change%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%2C%E2%80%99%20more%20accurately%20termed%20a%20socio-economic%20census%2C%20is%20not%20a%20mere%20head%20count%20of%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNot%20conducting%20a%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%20will%20not%20lead%20us%20anywhere%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20social%20justice.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20true%20that%20if%20you%20do%20a%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%2C%20you%20will%20necessarily%20get%20social%20justice%20out%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20He%20asserted%20that%20it%20is%20critical%20to%20not%20conflate%20the%20concept%20of%20justice%20with%20majoritarianism%20and%20the%20morality%20that%20is%20associated%20with%20large%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeshpande%20highlighted%20the%20dual%20challenge%20of%20addressing%20the%20needs%20of%20smaller%20or%20numerically%20minor%20castes%20from%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20without%20losing%20sight%20of%20the%20broader%20goal%20of%20social%20justice.%20The%20lecture%20delved%20into%20the%20historical%20context%2C%20the%20contemporary%20relevance%20of%20caste%20data%2C%20and%20the%20potential%20of%20such%20data%20to%20influence%20social%20and%20political%20dynamics.%20Deshpande%20raised%20critical%20questions%20about%20the%20representation%20and%20treatment%20of%20minority%20castes%2C%20the%20complexities%20of%20political%20mobilisation%20around%20caste%20identities%2C%20and%20the%20broader%20implications%20for%20social%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeshpande%20emphasised%20that%20publicly%20available%20socio-economic%20census%20data%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20transformative%20%E2%80%9Cawareness%20of%20numbers%2C%E2%80%9D%20that%20could%20generate%20a%20social%20force%20in%20its%20own%20right%2C%20potentially%20reshaping%20the%20political%20and%20social%20landscapes.%20Crucially%2C%20however%2C%20this%20force%20is%20but%20of%20tangential%20relevance%20to%20social%20justice%2C%20he%20pointed%20out.%20Drawing%20from%20historical%20precedents%20and%20recent%20developments%2C%20he%20unpacked%20the%20layered%20dynamics%20between%20caste%20enumeration%2C%20social%20justice%20policies%2C%20and%20the%20concept%20of%20majority%20versus.%20minority%20statuses%20within%20Indian%20society.%20The%20professor%20discussed%20the%20difference%20between%20knowing%20the%20numbers%20in%20an%20arithmetic%20sense%20and%20knowing%20it%20in%20a%20political%20sense%2C%20and%20the%20role%20of%20mechanisms%20like%20a%20census%20in%20crystallising%20identities%20and%20generating%20political%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeshpande%20argued%20against%20the%20tendency%20to%20conflate%20the%20notion%20of%20social%20justice%20with%20empirical%20data%20or%20evidence%20alone%2C%20and%20urged%20citizens%20to%20be%20mindful%20so%20that%20they%20do%20not%20get%20lost%20in%20the%20numbers.%20Illustratively%2C%20he%20spoke%20of%20the%20necessity%20to%20worry%20about%20the%20potential%20risks%20for%20the%20smaller%20castes%20located%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20social%20spectrum%2C%20in%20the%20grand%20calculus%20of%20social%20justice%E2%80%94how%20they%20might%20fare%20when%20the%20numbers%20reveal%20the%20realities%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmajority%E2%80%9D%20versus%20%E2%80%9Cminority%E2%80%9D.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20many%2Ffew%20and%20good%2Fless-good%20are%20socially%20constructed%2C%20not%20naturally%20occurring%20in%20the%20real%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCan%20we%20afford%20to%20have%20the%20claims%20of%20certain%20caste%20groups%20to%20be%20toned%20down%20in%20some%20way%20merely%20because%20they%20are%20smaller%20in%20number%3F%E2%80%9D%20asked%20Prof.%20Deshpande.%20This%20is%20of%20particular%20importance%20in%20the%20current%20political%20climate%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20where%20there%20is%20no%20room%20to%20speak%20of%20minority%20rights.%20Yet%2C%20he%20made%20his%20conviction%20unmistakably%20clear%20by%20asserting%20that%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20doing%20a%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%20will%20certainly%20not%20lead%20us%20in%20the%20direction%20towards%20social%20justice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lecture%20was%20a%20call%20to%20look%20deeper%2C%20an%20invitation%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthink%20about%20the%20associations%20we%20make%2C%20political%20and%20moral%2C%20between%20many-ness%20and%20few-ness%2C%20considering%20that%20the%20census%20is%20primarily%20a%20device%20to%20identify%20many-ness%20and%20few-ness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20professor%20expressed%20his%20concerns%20on%20whether%20merely%20recognising%20the%20numerical%20strength%20or%20weakness%20of%20certain%20castes%20could%20lead%20to%20reparative%20justice%2C%20or%20result%20in%20risking%20further%20reinforcement%20of%20existing%20prejudices.%20Responding%20to%20questions%20on%20why%20the%20headcount%20alone%20may%20not%20produce%20change%2C%20Deshpande%20said%20the%20audience%20to%20not%20forget%20that%20justice%20and%20injustice%20is%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20numbers%20alone.%20He%20argued%20that%20the%20demand%20for%20social%20justice%20does%20not%20come%20from%20belonging%20to%20any%20particular%20caste%2C%20but%20from%20the%20social%20reality%20that%20persons%20belonging%20to%20a%20particular%20caste%20are%20treated%20in%20a%20particular%20unjust%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20tension%20between%20economic%20status-based%20reservations%20(EWS)%20and%20caste-based%20reservations%2C%20Prof%20Deshpande%20reiterated%20the%20distinct%20nature%20of%20caste%20injustice%20that%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20economic%20disadvantage%20alone%2C%20emphasising%20the%20need%20for%20caste-sensitive%20policies.%20The%20nature%20of%20caste%20politics%20under%20Hindutva%20was%20discussed%20as%20well.%20Regarding%20the%20promise%20of%20a%20broader%20Hindutva%20umbrella%20under%20which%20caste%20would%20ceases%20to%20matter%2C%20Deshpande%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CCaste%20will%20not%20be%20defeated%20by%20Hindutva%2C%20given%20that%20it%20has%20been%20around%20for%20a%20few%20thousand%20years%20more%20than%20the%20Hindu%20identity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr.%20Awanish%20Kumar%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20faculty%20at%20the%20School%20of%20Development%2C%20Azim%20Premji%20University%2C%C2%A0%20who%20chaired%20the%20event%2C%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20debate%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98caste%20census%E2%80%99%20in%20India.%20He%20questioned%20its%20terminology%2C%20highlighting%20its%20historical%20roots%20and%20current%20relevance%2C%20notably%20through%20early%2020th-century%20efforts%20and%20recent%20Bihar%20survey%20findings.%20He%20underscored%20the%20importance%20of%20such%20data%20for%20understanding%20societal%20structures%20and%20for%20formulating%20development%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20event%E2%80%99s%20discussions%20illuminated%20the%20critical%20role%20of%20socio-economic%20census%20data%20in%20crafting%20informed%20social%20policies%2C%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20challenges%20and%20limitations%20inherent%20in%20using%20it%20alone%20to%20address%20India%E2%80%99s%20deep-rooted%20social%20inequalities.%20This%20dialogue%20underscored%20the%20ongoing%20need%20for%20a%20thoughtful%20engagement%20with%20caste%20dynamics%2C%20social%20justice%2C%20and%20the%20pursuit%20of%20equitable%20solutions%20in%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20diverse%20societies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESethu%20and%20Sai%20Chandan%20are%20researchers%20at%20the%20Foundation%20for%20Agrarian%20Studies%2C%20Bengaluru.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707561053000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%