0regulatory%20framework.%20Between%20November%2010%2C%202023%20and%20January%2015%20this%20year%2C%20the%20ministry%20carried%20out%20a%20public%20consultation%20seeking%20comments%20on%20the%20draft%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20media%20bodies%20expressed%20consternation%20over%20the%20upcoming%20law.%20Journalist%20bodies%20%E2%80%93%20The%20National%20Alliance%20of%20Journalists%20(NAJ)%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%2C%20and%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Working%20Journalists%20Federation%20(APWJF)%20join%20the%20Network%20of%20Women%20in%20Media%20India%2C%20(NWMI)%20and%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20others%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fgateway-to-censorship-journalist-bodies-express-concern-over-proposed-broadcasting-services-bill%5C%22%3Ehave%20expressed%20%E2%80%9Cgrave%20reservations%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20proposed%20law.%20They%20describe%20it%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgateway%20to%20censorship%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20joint%20statement%20the%20NAJ%2C%20DUJ%2C%20and%20APWJF%20say%20that%20this%20proposed%20Bill%20is%20a%20step%20further%20%E2%80%9Cto%20expanding%20a%20new%20era%20of%20undeclared%20censorship%E2%80%9D%20and%20increasing%20government%20control%20over%20all%20types%20of%20media%20from%20TV%20channels%2C%20to%20films%2C%20and%20platforms%20like%20Netflix%20and%20Prime%20Video%2C%20YouTube%2C%20radio%2C%20even%20Instagram%20and%20other%20social%20media%20platforms%20as%20well%20as%20news%20websites%20and%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20had%20written%20to%20Union%20information%20and%20broadcasting%20minister%20Anurag%20Thakur%20calling%20the%20draft%20of%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fvague-and-excessively-intrusive-editors-guild-of-india-to-centre-on-broadcast-services-bill%5C%22%3Evague%20and%20excessively%20intrusive%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%20The%20EGI%2C%20whose%20mandate%20is%20to%20%E2%80%9Cprotect%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20to%20raise%20standards%20of%20editorial%20leadership%E2%80%9D%20of%20news%20media%20outlets%2C%20had%20told%20the%20minister%20that%20the%20new%20Bill%20will%20prove%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20to%20the%20spirit%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcontrol-all-or-delete-the-draft-broadcast-bill-is-a-blueprint-for-censorship%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20that%20%E2%80%9Cas%20a%C2%A0charter%20for%20censorship%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmib.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FPublic%2520Notice_0.pdf%5C%22%3Ethe%20Broadcasting%20Services%20(Regulation)%20Bill%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Broadcast%20Bill)%20drafted%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Broadcasting%20(MIB)%20is%20a%20remarkable%20instrument%E2%80%A6%20this%20is%20an%20omnibus%20set%20of%20rules%20aimed%20at%20shutting%20down%20any%20news%20or%20views%20even%20mildly%20not%20in%20the%20service%20of%20those%20who%20happen%20to%20be%20in%20government%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707551036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F23203159%2FScreen-Shot-2020-10-23-at-8.31.43-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20communication%20and%20information%20technology%20said%20it%20would%20like%20to%20'engage%20in%20constructive%20discussions%20regarding%20the%20proposed%20draft%20legislation%20at%20a%20more%20mature%20stage%20of%20its%20formulation'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-tells-centre-to-expedite-passage-of-controversial-broadcasting-services-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Imran%20Khan%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Fight%20In%20Pak's%20Game%20Of%20Thrones%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20after%20long%20delays%20in%20results%20that%20prompted%20further%20allegations%20the%20military%20had%20engaged%20in%20vote-rigging%2C%20the%20army-backed%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20declared%20victory%20as%20the%20party%20with%20the%20largest%20number%20of%20seats.%20However%2C%20to%20form%20a%20government%2C%20the%20party%20founded%20by%20the%20three-time%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20will%20be%20forced%20to%20cut%20deals%20with%20rivals%20and%20independents.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20PPP%2C%20whose%20popularity%20is%20largely%20limited%20to%20its%20Sindh%20heartland%2C%20also%20did%20better%20than%20expected%2C%20with%20leader%20Bilawal%20Bhutto%20Zardari%20saying%20early%20results%20were%20%26quot%3Bvery%20encouraging%26quot%3B.%20The%20PML-N%20and%20PPP%20joined%20forces%20with%20minor%20parties%20to%20boot%20Khan%20from%20office%20in%20April%202022%20after%20his%20PTI%20had%20won%20a%20slender%20majority%20in%20the%202018%20election.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20enough%20of%20a%20majority%20to%20run%20the%20government%20ourselves%2C%20therefore%20we%20invite%20the%20other%20parties%20and%20candidates%20who%20have%20been%20successful%20to%20work%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sharif%20said%20at%20his%20party%20headquarters%20in%20Lahore.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImran%20Khan%20yesterday%20claimed%20victory%20in%20the%20general%20election%20in%20an%20audio-visual%20message%20created%20using%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20shared%20on%20his%20X%20social%20media%20account.%20Imran%20Khan%20heads%20the%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20(PTI).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20PTI%20had%20defied%20a%20months-long%20crackdown%20that%20crippled%20campaigning%20and%20forced%20their%20candidates%20to%20run%20as%20independents%20with%20a%20combined%20showing%20in%20Thursday's%20election%20that%20still%20challenged%20their%20chief%20rivals.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImran%20Khan%20also%20rejected%20rival%20Nawaz%20Sharif's%20earlier%20claim%20to%20victory.%20Khan%20called%20on%20his%20supporters%20to%20celebrate%20a%20win%20that%20was%20achieved%20despite%20what%20he%20calls%20a%20crackdown%20on%20his%20party.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20slow%20counting%20process%20showed%20independents%20had%20won%20at%20least%2099%20seats%20--%2088%20of%20them%20loyal%20to%20Khan%20--%20by%20Saturday%20morning.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPML-N%20took%2071%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20Peoples%20Party%20(PPP)%20snapped%20up%2053%2C%20with%2015%20of%20the%20elected%20266-seat%20National%20Assembly%20still%20to%20be%20announced.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMinor%20parties%20between%20them%20shared%2027%20seats%20--%20including%20the%20Muttahida%20Qaumi%20Movement%20(MQM)%2C%20which%20took%2017%20--%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20of%20great%20interest%20to%20PTI%20in%20coming%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20PTI's%20independents%20join%20one%20of%20them%2C%20they%20can%20take%20a%20share%20of%20the%20further%2070%20unelected%20seats%20reserved%20for%20women%20and%20religious%20minorities%2C%20which%20are%20allocated%20according%20to%20party%20performance%20in%20the%20contested%20vote.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20inputs%20from%20AFP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707550440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F6vsuj2v8_pakistan-election_625x300_10_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-election-2024-nawaz-sharif-bilawal-bhutto-join-hands-to-defeat-imran-khan-in-pakistan-election-2024-5030321%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pakistan%20faces%20days%20of%20political%20horse-trading%20after%20the%20final%20few%20election%20results%20released%20today%20showed%20no%20clear%20majority.%20Independent%20candidates%20loyal%20to%20jailed%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20showed%20a%20strong%20performance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-election-2024-nawaz-sharif-bilawal-bhutto-join-hands-to-defeat-imran-khan-in-pakistan-election-2024-5030321%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-election-2024-nawaz-sharif-bilawal-bhutto-join-hands-to-defeat-imran-khan-in-pakistan-election-2024-5030321%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-election-2024-nawaz-sharif-bilawal-bhutto-join-hands-to-defeat-imran-khan-in-pakistan-election-2024-5030321%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22K.%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20Incisive%20Essays%20on%20Caste%2C%20Communalism%20and%20Rise%20of%20State%20Authoritarianism%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EK.%20Balagopal%20was%20a%20civil%20rights%20activist%20and%20left-wing%20intellectual%20who%20was%20mainly%20active%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20from%20the%201980s%20until%20his%20death%20in%202009.%20In%20the%20nineties%2C%20he%20became%20increasingly%20critical%20of%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20War%20Group%2C%20with%20which%20he%20had%20been%20associated%2C%20and%20developed%20those%20criticisms%20at%20length%20in%20a%20famous%20Telugu%20essay%20called%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Darker%20Side%20of%20the%20Naxalite%20Movement%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0(%3Ci%3ECheekati%20Konalu%3C%2Fi%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2016%20essays%20and%20articles%20in%20this%20collection%20straddle%20the%20period%20from%201985%20to%202003.%20Those%20were%20years%20that%20saw%20growing%20caste%20violence%20against%20the%20rural%20poor%2C%20strident%20middle-class%20campaigns%20against%20reservation%2C%20the%20consolidation%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20as%20a%20mass%20political%20force%20working%20to%20transform%20India%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20state%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20a%20steady%20increase%20in%20state%20authoritarianism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20323px)%2085vw%2C%20323px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22323%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM.png%20593w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10125153%2FScreenshot-2024-02-10-at-12.48.35-PM-194x300.png%20194w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696487%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EK.%20Balagopal%2C%20Understanding%20Fascism%3A%20Writings%20on%20Caste%2C%20Class%20and%20the%20State%2C%3Cbr%3ECurated%20and%20introduced%20by%20V.%20Geetha.%3Cbr%3ESouth%20Side%20Books%2C%20Hyderabad%20(2023).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECaste%2C%20communalism%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20increasingly%20authoritarian%20state%2C%20therefore%2C%20seem%20like%20the%20natural%20rubrics%20under%20which%20to%20organise%20the%20articles%20and%20this%20is%20what%20editor%20V.%20Geetha%20has%20done.%20With%20a%20final%20exception%2C%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20endorsement%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECommunalism%20Combat%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20all%20of%20the%20articles%20were%20published%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEconomic%20and%20Political%20Weekly%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20pattern%20of%20caste%20violence%20described%20by%20Balagopal%20in%20the%20first%20two%20articles%20contains%20features%20which%20are%20worth%20highlighting%3A%20the%20atrocities%20occurred%20in%20the%20economically%20advanced%20coastal%20districts%20of%20Andhra%20where%20Kammas%20are%20the%20dominant%20agrarian%20community%3B%20the%20violence%20targeted%20Madigas%20and%20Malas%2C%20landless%20communities%20who%20work%20as%20farm%20servants%20and%20agricultural%20labourers%3B%20politically%2C%20the%20landed%20classes%20backed%20the%20Telugu%20Desam%20and%20its%20allies%20on%20the%20left%20and%20far%20right%2C%20while%20the%20Dalits%20supported%20Congress%20(I)%3B%20in%20Karamchedu%20in%20July%201985%20a%203000-strong%20mob%20of%20caste%20Hindus%20(viz.%20Kammas)%20assaulted%20the%20Madigas%20en%20masse%3B%20women%20were%20dragged%20out%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20stripped%20and%20molested%20or%20raped%3B%20at%20Chundur%20the%20police%20were%20%E2%80%9Cmute%20spectators%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20massacre%20that%20occurred%20in%20August%201991%3B%20and%20most%20importantly%2C%20the%20Malas%20and%20Madigas%20of%20the%20coastal%20districts%20%E2%80%9Care%20better%20educated%2C%20assertive%20and%20identity-conscious%20than%20other%20Dalit%20communities%20there%20or%20elsewhere%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%5BT%5Dhe%20younger%20generation%20has%20started%20rejecting%20the%20social%20and%20political%20subordination%20to%20the%20forward%20castes%20that%20has%20traditionally%20been%20the%20lot%20of%20the%20Dalits%E2%80%A6It%20is%20this%E2%80%A6assertiveness%20of%20the%20Malas%20and%20Madigas%20that%20the%20forward%20castes%20find%20so%20intolerable%2C%20leading%20to%20assaults%20such%20as%20Karamchedu%20and%20Chundur%E2%80%9D%20(p.23).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9990s%20Balagopal%20had%20come%20around%20to%20the%20view%20that%20%E2%80%9Ctrying%20to%20convince%20the%20lower%20middle%20class%20and%20middle%20class%20savarna%20farmers%20that%20their%20material%20interest%20lies%20in%20a%20class%20unity%20with%20Dalits%2C%20is%20a%20fruitless%20and%20pedantic%20solution%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETurning%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20reservation%2C%20Balagopal%20surmised%20in%201986%20that%20well%20over%20half%20of%20Andhra%E2%80%99s%20population%20consisted%20of%20the%20so-called%20Backward%20Castes%20(BCs).%20So%20when%20a%20commission%20appointed%20in%201982%20eventually%20recommended%20that%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20backward%20caste%20reservation%20share%20should%20be%20raised%20from%2025%25%20to%2044%25%20(assuming%20that%208%25%20of%20those%20castes%20could%20fend%20for%20themselves%20in%20their%20competition%20with%20the%20forward%20castes)%2C%20this%20sparked%20outrage%20among%20the%20forward%20castes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20course%2C%20%E2%80%9Coutrage%E2%80%9D%20of%20this%20sort%20is%20never%20spontaneous%20and%20has%20to%20be%20contrived%20or%20conjured%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20that%20used%20the%20anti-reservation%20campaigns%2C%20both%20here%20and%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20to%20build%20a%20base%20among%20the%20urban%20middle%20class.%20Students%20in%20the%20Akhil%20Bharatiya%20Vidya%20Parishad%20(ABVP)%20constituted%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20anti-reservation%20agitators%20in%20Andhra%2C%20with%20their%20base%20in%20the%20medical%20and%20engineering%20colleges.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20landed%20upper%20caste%20families%20these%20students%20came%20from%20had%2C%20by%20now%20(mid%20eighties)%2C%20coalesced%20into%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20rich%20Provincial%20Propertied%20Class%E2%80%9D.%20This%20new%20provincial%20bourgeoisie%20was%20far%20better%20organised%20than%20the%20backward%20castes%20because%20the%20forward%20castes%20of%20which%20it%20was%20made%20up%20were%20more%20widely%20spread%20across%20the%20state%20and%20used%20their%20extensive%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecaste%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20links%20to%20mobilise%20their%20lower%20middle-class%20caste-fellows%20as%20the%20mass%20base%20of%20vociferous%20resistance%20to%20affirmative%20action.%20%E2%80%9CFoot%20soldiers%20of%20fascism%E2%80%9D%20was%20how%20Balagopal%20described%20the%20latter%20in%20probably%20his%20earliest%20reference%20to%20this.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFour%20years%20later%2C%20an%20article%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThis%20Anti-Mandal%20Mania%3C%2Fem%3E%20saw%20reservations%20as%20so%20threatening%20because%20they%20attacked%20the%20caste%20system.%20%E2%80%9CCaste%20is%20juridically%20dead%2C%20but%20very%20much%20alive%20politically%20and%20ideologically%E2%80%A6Tickets%20to%20the%20Assembly%20or%20Parliament%20at%20election%20time%2C%20public%20works%20and%20excise%20contracts%2C%20co-operative%20loans%2C%20industrial%20licenses%2C%20supply%20contracts%2C%20managerial%20jobs%20in%20the%20private%20sector%E2%80%A6not%20one%20of%20these%20is%20obtained%20without%20the%20use%20of%20caste%E2%80%9D%20(p.58).%20Caste%2C%20Balagopal%20argued%2C%20was%20a%20mode%20of%20reproduction%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20class%2C%20an%20%E2%80%9Cunwritten%20reservation%20that%20the%20forward%20castes%20enjoy%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9Cconnections%E2%80%9D%E2%80%9D%20and%20incomparably%20more%20powerful%20than%20any%20of%20Mandal%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20(p.59).%20But%20of%20course%20%E2%80%9C%5Bt%5Dhe%20casteism%20of%20the%20forward%20castes%20is%20never%20seen%20as%20casteism%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20Balagopal%20used%20this%20analysis%20of%20the%20functionality%20of%20caste%20to%20the%20governance%20of%20class%20relations%20to%20defend%20the%20sort%20of%20identity%20politics%20that%20would%20emerge%20in%20the%201990s.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20remains%E2%80%A6the%20political%20duty%20of%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20deprived%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eto%20use%20their%20caste%20identity%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20their%20liberation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D.%20Caste%20and%20class%20struggles%20were%20%E2%80%9Cclosely%20interwoven%20and%20coterminous%20struggles%E2%80%9D%20(p.63).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%20five%20essays%20that%20confront%20%E2%80%9CHindutva%E2%80%9D%20in%20part%20two%20of%20the%20book%2C%20much%20of%20the%20focus%20is%20on%20the%20Indian%20lower-middle%20class.%20The%20cult%20of%20Ayyappa%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20latest%20mass-god%20of%20Hinduism%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20grounded%20socially%20in%20a%20growing%20lower%20middle%20class%20whose%20insecurities%2C%20Balagopal%20sensed%2C%20were%20fuelling%20all%20manner%20of%20reactions%2C%20from%20the%20proliferation%20of%20cults%20%E2%80%9Coutside%E2%80%9D%20the%20establishment%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20mafias%20and%20gangsterism%20in%20the%20towns.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBalagopal%20was%20a%20prescient%20writer%20and%20anticipated%20the%20way%20these%20various%20rebellions%20could%20be%20absorbed%20and%20reintegrated%20in%20the%20groundswell%20of%20what%20this%20article%20describes%20(in%201989)%20as%20%E2%80%9Cemerging%20fascist%20trends%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdeveloping%20fascism%E2%80%9D.%20He%20referred%20to%20cults%20such%20as%20that%20at%20Sabarimalai%20being%20appropriated%20for%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20purposes%E2%80%9D%2C%20to%20the%20influx%20of%20agrarian%20wealth%20into%20Vijaywada%20creating%20a%20fertile%20basis%20for%20the%20operation%20of%20mafias%20in%20real%20estate%20and%20finance%2C%20and%20to%20the%20class%20hatred%20unleashed%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvulgar%20new%20rich%20of%20coastal%20Andhra%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20the%20trail%20of%20anti-Kamma%20violence%20left%20behind%20by%20riots%20in%20that%20port%20city.%20And%20the%20eighties%20saw%20a%20proliferation%20of%20repressive%20laws%20that%20only%20reinforced%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgradual%20demise%20of%20every%20one%20of%20the%20institutions%20of%20bourgeois%20democracy%E2%80%9D%20(p.93).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBalagopal%E2%80%99s%201993%20piece%20on%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20is%20probably%20where%20his%20conception%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20Indian%20fascism%20comes%20through%20most%20clearly.%20This%20was%20where%20he%20argued%20that%20Hindutva%20%E2%80%9Chas%20its%20origin%20in%20a%20political%20need%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecounter%20aspirations%20for%20democracy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9D%20.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20mass%20base%20was%20constructed%20out%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cresentment%20and%20frustration%20born%20in%20reaction%20to%20the%20space%20conquered%20by%20the%20oppressed%20and%20the%20underprivileged%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20universe%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20he%20insisted%20that%20there%20was%20no%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erevolution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20going%20on%20in%20India%20to%20warrant%20describing%20Hindutva%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccounter-revolution%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20has%20been%20a%20tremendous%20expansion%20of%20democratic%20and%20egalitarian%20aspirations%20among%20the%20oppressed%20people%E2%80%9D.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20if%20democracy%E2%80%99s%20right%20arm%20was%20fettered%20to%20a%20state%20apparatus%20that%20thrived%20on%20a%20culture%20of%20repression%2C%20its%20constitutional%20left%20arm%20allowed%20for%20a%20culture%20of%20freedom%20that%20nurtured%20aspirations%20for%20equality%2C%20justice%20and%20self-respect%20among%20the%20mass%20of%20working%20people.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20Hindutva%20was%20nonetheless%20capable%20of%20attracting%20%E2%80%9Csignificant%20support%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmiddle%20and%20lower%20levels%20of%20society%E2%80%9D%2C%20this%2C%20Balagopal%20suggested%2C%20was%20because%20society%20was%20characterised%20by%20a%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20hierarchy%20more%20than%20it%20was%20by%20any%20simple%20bipolarity%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BT%5Dhe%20smallest%20farmer%20thinks%20he%20is%20superior%20to%20the%20wage%20labourer%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20BJP%20was%20adept%20at%20making%20this%20sense%20of%20hierarchy%20(recursive%20inequalities)%20a%20source%20of%20resentment%20at%20the%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cpampering%E2%80%9D%20of%20workers%2C%20women%2C%20untouchables%2C%20Muslims%20and%20so%20on.%20Whatever%20one%20thinks%20of%20this%20explanation%2C%20by%202002%20it%20was%20not%20resentment%20but%20outright%20hatred%20that%20loomed%20large%20in%20Balaglopal%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20of%20communalism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20common%20Hindu%E2%80%99s%20hatred%20for%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20Muslims%E2%80%A6is%20the%20only%20thing%20alive%20in%20Gujarat%20today%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20June%20that%20year.%20Indeed%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20very%20large%20number%20of%20Hindus%20all%20over%20the%20country%20harbour%20an%20extraordinary%20hatred%20for%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20reflections%20on%20the%20ghastly%20pogroms%20that%20tore%20through%20Gujarat%20in%202002%20are%20an%20extraordinary%20piece%20of%20writing%20%E2%80%93%20not%20just%20for%20the%20rawness%20of%20the%20emotion%20expressed%20there%20but%20because%2C%20to%20his%20credit%2C%20he%20was%20willing%20to%20confront%20what%20he%20called%20%E2%80%9Cuncomfortable%20questions%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20participation%20of%20Adivasis%20and%20Dalits%20in%20the%20rioting%2C%20looting%20and%20killing%20is%20one%20such%20%5Bquestion%5D%E2%80%A6In%20all%20the%20areas%20along%20the%20north-eastern%20border%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%A6there%20was%20sizeable%20participation%20of%20Adivasis%20along%20with%20non-Adivasis%20in%20the%20violence.%20The%20two%20were%20part%20of%20the%20same%20mob%20in%20most%20cases%E2%80%9D.%20So%20too%20with%20Dalits.%20%E2%80%9CDalit%20participation%20in%20the%20violence%20at%20Ahmedabad%20is%20even%20less%20ambiguous.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20Dalit%20youth%20took%20direct%20part%20in%20the%20gruesome%20violence%20of%20that%20city%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20This%20was%20a%20frontal%20challenge%20to%20the%20unrestrained%20defence%20of%20identity%20politics%20he%20had%20advocated%20as%20late%20as%201990%2C%20and%20to%20essentialist%20constructions%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%E2%80%9D%20Advasi%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%E2%80%9D%20Dalit.%20The%20manipulation%20of%20identities%20is%20of%20course%20the%20heart%20of%20fascist%20politics%20and%20Balagopal%20knew%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparticipation%E2%80%9D%20of%20these%20communities%20in%20the%20pogroms%20had%20everything%20to%20do%20with%20the%20organising%20drives%20of%20the%20Sangh%20parivar.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Vanavasi%20Kalyan%20Samiti%20of%20the%20Vishwa%20Hindu%20Parishad%20has%20made%20considerable%20inroads%20into%20the%20Adivasi%20areas%E2%80%A6every%20Adivasi%20village%20has%20at%20least%20one%20VHP%20activist%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Adivasis%20are%20%E2%80%9Cmade%20to%20feel%20that%20they%20are%20Hindus%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20collection%20ends%20with%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20scathing%20critique%20of%20the%20ineluctable%20ways%20in%20which%20the%20once%20beating%20heart%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%20has%20been%20progressively%20stifled%20by%20a%20slew%20of%20laws%20and%20repressive%20practices%20that%20have%20systematically%20undermined%20the%20rights%20of%20individuals%20under%20the%20Indian%20constitution.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20terror%20emanating%20from%20minorities%20alone%20is%20depicted%20as%20terror%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20wrote%20about%20both%20TADA%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20replication%20of%20its%20political%20and%20communal%20biases.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20how%20do%20we%20blend%20these%20different%20strands%20of%20the%20argument%20into%20a%20coherent%20idea%20of%20Indian%20fascism%3F%20The%20conception%20that%20best%20captures%20what%20Balagopal%20was%20driving%20at%20is%20Marcuse%E2%80%99s%20notion%20of%20fascism%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpreventive%20counterrevolution%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.versobooks.com%2Fen-gb%2Fproducts%2F2627-late-fascism%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlberto%20Toscano%20has%20foregrounded%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20in%20a%20fascinating%20chapter%20of%20his%20recent%20book%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELate%20Fascism%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(Verso%2C%202023).%20All%20of%20the%20moments%20that%20Marcuse%20listed%20in%20a%201970%20interview%20with%20Hans%20Magnus%20Enzensberger%20as%20markers%20of%20an%20incipient%20fascism%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20gradual%20or%20rapid%20abolition%20of%20the%20remnants%20of%20the%20constitutional%20state%E2%80%A6granting%20the%20police%20extraordinary%20legal%20powers%E2%80%A6the%20court%20decisions%20of%20recent%20years%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20almost%20direct%20censorship%20of%20the%20press%2C%20television%20and%20radio%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20these%20have%20been%20pivotal%20moments%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20political%20transformation%20since%20the%201980s.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20point%20of%20this%20unlikely%20comparison%20is%20not%20the%20analogy%2C%20but%20the%20insight%20it%20offers%20in%20suggesting%20that%20like%20the%20US%20(or%20Israel%20for%20that%20matter)%2C%20India%20has%20its%20own%20version(s)%20of%20%E2%80%9Cracialised%20state%20terror%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0and%20this%20or%20these%20versions%20is%20where%20we%20have%20to%20start%20in%20trying%20to%20%E2%80%9Cunderstand%20fascism%E2%80%9D%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EViewed%20in%20this%20light%2C%20Balagopal%E2%80%99s%20essays%20and%20the%20editor%E2%80%99s%20work%20in%20putting%20them%20together%20in%20this%20way%20become%20seminal%20contributions%20to%20grasping%20the%20nature%20of%20fascism%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EJairus%C2%A0Banaji%20is%20with%20the%20Department%20of%20Development%20Studies%2C%20SOAS%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20His%20most%20recent%20book%20is%20called%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3EWanting%20Something%20Completely%20Different%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0(Rab-Rab%2C%20Helsinki%2C%202023).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707550084000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30123722%2FIllustration-Pariplab-Chakraborty.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fk-balagopals-incisive-essays-on-caste-communalism-and-rise-of-state-authoritarianism-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20author%E2%80%99s%20pieces%20on%20Hindutva%20in%20the%201980s%20had%20forecast%20many%20of%20the%20trends%20that%20are%20visible%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fk-balagopals-incisive-essays-on-caste-communalism-and-rise-of-state-authoritarianism-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Virat%20Kohli%3A%20India%20batter%20to%20miss%20rest%20of%20England%20Test%20series%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707547890000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Flive-experience%2Fcps%2F624%2Fcpsprodpb%2F1725B%2Fproduction%2F_132611849_gettyimages-1761632661.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fsport%2Fcricket%2F68234342%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20batter%20Virat%20Kohli%20will%20miss%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Test%20series%20against%20England%20for%20personal%20reasons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A62%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fsport%2Fcricket%2F68234342%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fsport%2Fcricket%2F68234342.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fsport%2Fcricket%2F68234342.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cinema%20Paradiso%3A%20What%20Kashmir%20Lived%2C%20Longed%20for%20and%20Whispered%20of%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09170520%2F13191305844_0ef054e2b9_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20if%20anyone%20ever%20asked%20Mr.%20Maniktala%20if%20it%20was%20alright%20for%20the%20whole%20neighbourhood%20to%20descend%20on%20his%20place%20to%20watch%20the%20film%20on%20Doordarshan%20every%20Sunday%20evening.%20In%20the%20early%2070s%2C%20he%20was%20the%20bureau%20chief%20of%20the%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20and%20also%20the%20proud%20owner%20of%20the%20only%20television%20set%20in%20the%20whole%20state%20owned%20housing%20colony%20of%20Pratap%20Park%2C%20Residency%20Road.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEvery%20Sunday%20at%206%20pm%2C%20the%20entire%20neighbourhood%2C%20with%20the%20exception%20of%20some%20elderly%20gentlemen%2C%20would%20land%20up%20religiously%20at%20No.%202%2C%20Pratap%20Park.%20As%20the%20signature%20tune%20of%20Doordarshan%20filtered%20out%20onto%20the%20lanes%2C%20all%20the%20children%20would%20scurry%20down%20the%20streets%2C%20followed%20by%20their%20mothers%2C%20brothers%2C%20sisters%2C%20and%2C%20in%20my%20case%2C%20aunts%20and%20cousins%20too%2C%20to%20find%20the%20best%20seat%20in%20the%20house.%20The%20corridor%20outside%20their%20living%20room%2C%20a%20sea%20of%20footwear.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInside%2C%20the%20room%20would%20fill%20with%20anticipatory%20chatter%2C%20while%20the%20movie%20of%20the%20week%20was%20announced%20by%20probably%20the%20most%20well%20known%20face%20in%20the%20valley%2C%20a%20woman%20called%20Naseem%20Khan.%20The%20opening%20credits%20would%20be%20read%20aloud%20by%20all%20those%20who%20could.%20But%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20film%20started%2C%20the%20audience%20would%20be%20unable%20to%20take%20our%20eyes%20off%20the%20black%20and%20white%20images%20%E2%80%93%20each%20transported%20into%20our%20own%20dream%20world.%20Copious%20amounts%20of%20tears%2C%20hearty%20laughs%20at%20all%20the%20funny%20lines%2C%20and%20the%20rush%20of%20adrenaline%20as%20the%20bad%20guys%20got%20their%20due%20from%20the%20honest%2C%20upright%20hero%20%E2%80%93%20that%20was%20us.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20films%20screened%20on%20state-run%20television%20from%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%20were%20almost%20invariably%20about%20the%20protagonist%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20against%20poverty%2C%20and%20the%20effect%20it%20had%20on%20his%20relationships%20with%20his%20family%20or%20the%20love%20of%20his%20life.%20Inevitably%2C%20the%20hero%20triumphed%20against%20all%20odds.%20He%20did%20this%20by%20sticking%20to%20his%20principles%20to%20overcome%20the%20zamindar%20or%20the%20money%20lender%20or%20the%20factory%20owner.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20the%20villains%20belonged%20to%20the%20rich%20upper%20class%2C%20whereas%20the%20hero%20was%20from%20a%20rural%2C%20lower-middle%2C%20or%20working%20class.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20were%20the%20stories%20from%20the%20glory%20days%20of%20Nehruvian%20socialism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201976%2C%20my%20father%20bought%20our%20first%20TV%20set%2C%20a%20Telerad%20that%20came%20with%20its%20own%20wooden%20cabinet.%20The%20neighbourhood%20split%20into%20two%20audiences.%20If%20I%20remember%20correctly%2C%20nobody%20ever%20asked%20my%20parents%20either%20if%20it%20was%20alright%20to%20barge%20in%20and%20watch%20the%20weekly%20film%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EChitrahaar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20show%20which%20featured%20film%20songs.%20And%20yet%2C%20they%20did%20barge%20in.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quarters%20and%20apartment%20blocks%20on%20Residency%20Road%20housed%20mainly%20journalists%20and%20some%20bureaucrats.%20Some%20of%20these%20people%20were%20non-Kashmiris%20and%20this%20contributed%20to%20making%20this%20a%20vibrant%20place.%20We%20were%20exposed%20to%20a%20bigger%20culture%20of%20news%20and%20politics%20at%20a%20very%20young%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20State%20Motor%20Garages%20was%20located%20here%20and%20housed%20all%20the%20government%20cars%20meant%20for%20VIPs%2C%20state%20officials%20and%20sundry%20dignitaries%2C%20At%20times%2C%20it%20became%20our%20playground.%20There%20were%20old%20open-top%20Cadillacs%20and%20Chevrolet%20Impalas%20and%20even%20a%20Volkswagen%20van%20that%20had%20a%20bed%20and%20a%20kitchenette%20inside.%20On%20quiet%20weekends%2C%20some%20of%20us%20would%20play%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Echor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E-police%2C%20enacting%20mock%20car%20chases%20and%20shootouts%20or%20digging%20the%20dirt%20for%20treasure%20behind%20the%20staff%20quarters.%20Most%20of%20the%20time%20we%20came%20up%20with%20glass%20bottoms%20of%20alcohol%20bottles%20as%20booty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20in%20this%20very%20neighbourhood%20that%20I%20got%20cast%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20a%20tele%20film%20for%20Doordarshan%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEk%20Kahani%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20was%20four%20years%20old.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0Our%20home%20became%20a%20film%20set%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20days.%20All%20my%20scenes%20were%20shot%20there.%20I%20remember%20crying%20before%20every%20shot%20and%20it%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20cajoling%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20crew%20to%20calm%20me%20down%20with%20sweets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubconsciously%20the%20acting%20bug%20must%20have%20bitten%20me%20as%20lines%20between%20films%20and%20life%20blurred%20often%2C%20such%20as%20when%20I%20told%20off%20a%20relative%20who%20called%20me%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaaji%20gobur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98mama%E2%80%99s%20boy%E2%80%99%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAap%20ko%20kya%20pata%20Ma%20ka%20pyar%20kya%20hota%20hai%2C%20mamta%20kya%20hoti%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESubconsciously%20the%20acting%20bug%20must%20have%20bitten%20me%20as%20lines%20between%20films%20and%20life%20blurred%20often%2C%20such%20as%20when%20I%20told%20off%20a%20relative%20who%20called%20me%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaaji%20gobur%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98mama%E2%80%99s%20boy%E2%80%99%20with%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAap%20ko%20kya%20pata%20Ma%20ka%20pyar%20kya%20hota%20hai%2C%20mamta%20kya%20hoti%20hai%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOr%20when%20a%20frustrated%20policeman%2C%20during%20the%20agitation%20in%20the%20summer%20of%201985%20against%20G.M.%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20government%20hit%20me%20with%20his%20lathi%20for%20no%20reason%2C%20only%20to%20be%20given%20an%20expletives%20riddled%20monologue%20in%20English%2C%20on%20police%20brutality.%20I%20still%20remember%20the%20flabbergasted%20look%20on%20our%20neighbour%20and%20senior%20journalist%20Sham%20Koul%E2%80%99s%20face%20as%20he%20pulled%20me%20away%20from%20further%20harm.%20Little%20did%20he%20know%20that%20I%20had%20watched%20Al%20Pacino%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20Justice%20For%20All%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20VHS%20from%20the%20Oscar%20Video%20Library%20in%20Lal%20Chowk.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20uncle%2C%20Shamim%20Ahmed%20Shamim%2C%20published%20and%20edited%20an%20anti-establishment%20Urdu%20weekly%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAina%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(Mirror)%2C%20from%20a%20three-room%20extension%20behind%20the%20house%20that%20I%20was%20born%20in.%20He%20had%20been%20elected%20a%20member%20of%20Parliament%20in%201971%20as%20an%20independent%20and%20was%20considered%20a%20great%20orator%20in%20Urdu%20alongside%20the%20likes%20of%20A.B.%20Vajpayee%20in%20Hindi%20and%20Piloo%20Modi%20in%20English.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20uncle%20was%20the%20most%20well%20known%20person%20in%20our%20family%2C%20and%20his%20fame%20brought%20him%20in%20contact%20with%20other%20famous%20people.%20So%20not%20only%20did%20I%20see%20his%20photographs%20with%20great%20leaders%20of%20his%20time%20like%20the%20socialist%20dynamo%20Jai%20Prakash%20Narayan%20but%20also%20some%20big%20names%20from%20the%20film%20world.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165057%2Fimage_123650291-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22997%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165057%2Fimage_123650291-1.jpg%20997w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165057%2Fimage_123650291-1-300x239.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696396%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22795%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20author%E2%80%99s%20uncle%20Shamim%2C%20with%20JP.%20Photo%20courtesy%3A%20Aamir%20Bashir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20mother%20had%20a%20framed%20photograph%20of%20her%20standing%20beside%20the%20great%20Dilip%20Kumar%20and%20his%20wife%20and%20actress%20Saira%20Bano%2C%20and%20it%20obviously%20occupied%20pride%20of%20place%20in%20our%20modest%20drawing%20room.%20She%20had%20met%20them%20thanks%20to%20her%20brother%2C%20when%20they%20were%20visiting%20the%20valley.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESeeing%20that%20picture%2C%20I%20too%20had%20a%20burning%20ambition%20to%20be%20photographed%20alongside%20a%20film%20star%2C%20and%20of%20course%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20was%20my%20first%20preference.%20I%20came%20very%20close%20to%20fulfilling%20this%20ambition%20at%20a%20very%20young%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165037%2Fimage_123650291-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165037%2Fimage_123650291-2.jpg%20984w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165037%2Fimage_123650291-2-300x284.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696394%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22930%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20author%E2%80%99s%20mother%20on%20the%20left%20with%20Dilip%20Kumar%20and%20Saira%20Bano.%20Photo%20courtesy%3A%20Aamir%20Bashir%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFilm%20shoots%20were%20a%20common%20occurrence%20in%20the%20valley%20and%20one%20could%20easily%20become%20a%20spectator.%20But%20I%20had%20a%20trump%20card.%20Amitabh%E2%80%99s%20then%20personal%20assistant%2C%20Ravi%20Sharma%20was%20my%20neighbour.%20Ravi%20Bhaiyya%20was%20a%20thorough%20gentleman%20and%20also%20in%20my%20pre-%20adolescent%20eyes%2C%20the%20most%20glamorous%20person%20in%20the%20neighbourhood.%20He%20used%20to%20visit%20his%20parents%20and%20younger%20brother%20occasionally%20and%20whenever%20he%20did%2C%20my%20cousins%20and%20I%20would%20land%20up%20at%20his%20place%20to%20ask%20him%20about%20Amitabh%20and%20the%20various%20locations%20around%20the%20world%20he%20had%20been%20to%2C%20on%20film%20shoots%20with%20him.%20I%20remember%20clearly%2C%20that%20my%20first%20ever%20piece%20of%20Swiss%20chocolate%20was%20given%20to%20me%20by%20Ravi%20Bhaiyya.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20one%20of%20his%20visits%20home%2C%20Amitabh%20too%20was%20in%20town%2C%20to%20shoot%20another%20of%20his%20blockbusters%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESatte%20Pe%20Satta%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20(which%20was%20a%20copy%20of%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESeven%20Brides%20for%20Seven%20Brothers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E).%20We%20pestered%20Ravi%20for%20days%20to%20set%20up%20an%20audience%20with%20the%20star.%20Finally%20a%20date%20and%20time%20was%20set.%20It%20was%20around%207%20in%20the%20evening%20when%20about%20eight%20or%20nine%20kids%20from%20the%20neighbourhood%20squeezed%20into%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20old%20rickety%20Fiat%20and%20rode%20to%20the%20Oberoi%20Palace%20Hotel%2C%20where%20filming%20was%20taking%20place.%20I%20vividly%20recall%20that%20our%20car%20was%20stopped%20by%20guards%20at%20some%20distance%20from%20the%20film%20set.%20My%20father%20asked%20them%20about%20Ravi%20and%20we%20were%20asked%20to%20wait.%20While%20we%20waited%20for%20Ravi%20to%20come%20and%20escort%20us%20for%20our%20private%20audience%20with%20Amitabh%2C%20we%20caught%20a%20glimpse%20of%20him%20contemplatively%20pacing%20up%20and%20down%2C%20wearing%20a%20brown%20leather%20jacket%20and%20cream-coloured%20trousers%2C%20which%20were%20tucked%20into%20his%20cowboy%20boots.%20The%20excitement%20levels%20inside%20the%20car%20were%20naturally%20through%20the%20roof.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Ravi%20Bhaiyya%20went%20to%20inform%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20of%20our%20arrival%2C%20we%20were%20almost%20ready%20to%20jump%20out%20of%20the%20car%20and%20race%20up%20to%20him.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20the%20first%20to%20shake%20his%20hand.%20The%20two%20minutes%20that%20Ravi%20Bhaiyya%20took%20to%20come%20back%20to%20us%20seemed%20like%20a%20lifetime.%20He%20did%20return%2C%20only%20to%20sheepishly%20tell%20us%20that%20a%20meeting%20would%20not%20be%20possible%20as%20the%20actor%20was%20tired.%20I%20could%20almost%20hear%20the%20several%20young%20hearts%20shatter%20in%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20car.%20Why%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20did%20not%20hear%20them%2C%20god%20only%20knows%2C%20for%20some%20of%20us%20were%20howling%20loud%20enough.%20I%20was%20eight%20then.%20Undeterred%2C%20I%20remained%20an%20Amitabh%20fan%20through%20most%20of%20my%20teens.%20The%20%E2%80%98angry%20young%20man%E2%80%99%20phase%20of%20films%20that%20made%20him%20a%20star%20left%20a%20deep%20impression%20on%20me%2C%20and%20an%20even%20deeper%20suspicion%20of%20the%20powerful%20and%20power%20structures%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Bombay%20film%20parlance%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccut%20to%E2%80%9D%20some%2025%20years%20later.%20I%20was%20acting%20in%20my%20first%20big%20budget%20Bollywood%20film%20with%20several%20big%20name%20stars%2C%20including%20the%20%E2%80%9CBig%20B%E2%80%9D%20as%20he%20was%20now%20popularly%20known.%20A%20lot%20of%20water%20had%20flowed%20under%20the%20proverbial%20bridge%20since%20that%20night%20at%20the%20Oberoi%20Palace.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20no%20longer%20a%20Bollywood%20fan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09173832%2Fbicycle-thieves-1200-1200-675-675-crop-000000.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09173832%2Fbicycle-thieves-1200-1200-675-675-crop-000000.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09173832%2Fbicycle-thieves-1200-1200-675-675-crop-000000-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09173832%2Fbicycle-thieves-1200-1200-675-675-crop-000000-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696408%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Bicycle%20Thieves%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWatching%20Vittorio%20De%20Sica%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBicycle%20Thieves%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20at%20the%20Shakuntalam%20Theater%20in%20Pragati%20Maidan%20in%20Delhi%20was%20a%20turning%20point.%20Through%20the%20theft%20of%20a%20humble%20bicycle%2C%20De%20Sica%20wove%20the%20tale%20of%20socio-economic%20conditions%20in%20post%20war%20Italy.%20I%20realised%20that%20cinema%20could%20be%20a%20time%20capsule%20and%20films%20could%20be%20timeless.%20I%20made%20it%20a%20point%20to%20devour%20as%20many%20foreign%20films%20as%20I%20could%20during%20the%20International%20Film%20Festival%20at%20Siri%20Fort%20in%20Delhi.%20I%20had%20seen%20films%20by%20such%20great%20masters%20as%20De%20Sica%2C%20Fellini%2C%20Antonioni%2C%20Godard%20and%20Truffaut%2C%20Szabo%2C%20Kurosawa%20and%20of%20course%20the%20greats%20%E2%80%93%20Satyajit%20Ray%2C%20Ritwik%20Ghatak%20and%20others%20of%20our%20own%20%E2%80%9Cparallel%20cinema%E2%80%9D%20movement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20now%20a%20professional%20actor.%20And%20yet%2C%20as%20I%20stood%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Big%20B%2C%20for%20my%20introductory%20scene%2C%20it%20all%20came%20crumbling%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20were%20on%20the%20sets%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EArmaan%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20Mussoorie%20and%20this%20was%20my%20one%20and%20only%20scene%20with%20Amitabh%20Bachchan.%20As%20we%20rehearsed%20for%20the%20master%20shot%2C%20I%20forgot%20one%20of%20my%20lines%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20seem%20to%20affect%20Amitabh.%20He%20was%20very%20thorough%20and%20rigorous%20in%20his%20preparation.%20I%20myself%20was%20in%20my%20own%20world%2C%20sliding%20down%20the%20slippery%20slope%20of%20paranoia.%20We%20rehearsed%20the%20short%20scene%20several%20times%20and%20after%20each%20rehearsal%2C%20I%20believed%20that%20I%20was%20sounding%20more%20and%20more%20like%20Amitabh.%20Here%20I%20was%2C%20a%20young%20actor%2C%20getting%20his%20big%20break%20in%20Bollywood%20and%20I%20was%20going%20to%20blow%20it!%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20exposed%20as%20an%20actor.%20I%20would%20be%20known%20as%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20mimic.%20In%20the%20end%20it%20was%20Amitabh%20himself%20who%20came%20to%20my%20rescue.%20Just%20before%20the%20shot%20was%20to%20roll%2C%20he%20reminded%20me%20of%20having%20forgotten%20my%20line%20during%20one%20of%20the%20rehearsals.%20I%20felt%20a%20chill%20in%20my%20spine%20and%20went%20completely%20numb%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20much%20recollection%20of%20what%20happened%20after%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESrinagar%20in%20those%20days%20had%20around%207-8%20cinemas.%20Regal%20and%20Palladium%20were%20walking%20distance%20from%20my%20house.%20Then%20there%20was%20Khayyam%2C%20Naaz%2C%20Shiraz%2C%20Neelam%2C%20Firdaus%20and%20Broadway.%20The%20first%20film%20I%20ever%20saw%20in%20a%20cinema%20hall%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESholay%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20our%20domestic%20help%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Mohiuddin%2C%20a%20movie%20buff.%20Funnily%20enough%20I%20already%20knew%20the%20story%20of%20the%20film%20and%20even%20remembered%20some%20dialogues%20thanks%20to%20Mohiuddin%20who%20had%20seen%20it%20several%20times%2C%20and%20narrated%20the%20story%2C%20scene-by-scene%2C%20while%20preparing%20dinner%20one%20late%20afternoon.%20With%20my%20parents%20working%20and%20me%20and%20my%20brother%20in%20school%2C%20Mohiuddin%20used%20to%20often%20catch%20an%20afternoon%20show.%20He%20would%20then%20narrate%20the%20entire%20film%20in%20his%20baritone%20voice%20to%20me%20in%20the%20kitchen%20while%20preparing%20the%20evening%20meal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fthree-decades-after-militancy-closed-cinemas-in-kashmir-srinagar-readies-for-its-first-multiplex%5C%22%3EThree%20Decades%20After%20Militancy%20Closed%20Cinemas%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20Srinagar%20Readies%20for%20its%20First%20Multiplex%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20other%20privilege%20I%20had%20thanks%20to%20my%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20newspaper%20is%20that%20I%20got%20press%20passes%20to%20watch%20films%20in%20the%20local%20cinemas.%20Otherwise%20I%20would%E2%80%99ve%20been%20deprived%20of%20all%20the%20films%20that%20came%20into%20town.%20There%20was%20no%20culture%20of%20queuing%20up%20to%20buy%20tickets%20in%20those%20days.%20You%20either%20had%20to%20risk%20serious%20bodily%20harm%20or%20buy%20the%20tickets%20in%20black%20from%20a%20%E2%80%9Cblacker%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20tout.%20Young%20men%20climbed%20up%20a%20human%20pyramid%20with%20nothing%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20except%20a%20bare%20wall%2C%20and%20then%20make%20their%20way%20down%20to%20a%20pigeon%20hole%20in%20the%20wall%20%E2%80%93%20that%20was%20the%20box%20office%20window.%20This%2C%20to%20buy%20a%20ticket%20worth%20Rs%202.50.%20That%2C%20plus%20bruised%20and%20bloodied%20wrists%20and%20forearms%20is%20what%20it%20cost%20to%20watch%20a%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ekhel%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Efilim%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20front%20rows%20of%20the%20stalls%20or%20%E2%80%9Cthird%E2%80%9D%20as%20it%20was%20called%20in%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20almost%20every%20week%20I%20would%20go%20either%20to%20Regal%20or%20Palladium%20cinema%2C%20which%20were%20walking%20distance%20from%20my%20house.%20But%20very%20rarely%20did%20I%20go%20with%20my%20parents%20to%20watch%20movies%20anymore.%20The%20days%20of%20watching%20black%20and%20white%20films%20with%20my%20family%20and%20the%20entire%20neighbourhood%20were%20over%3B%20%2C%20cinema%20now%20became%20a%20more%20private%20and%20intimate%20experience.%20And%20it%20was%20in%20colour!%20Mohiuddin%20would%20inform%20me%20of%20the%20latest%20film%20running%20in%20the%20neighbourhood%20and%20I%E2%80%99d%20ask%20my%20mother%20to%20arrange%20a%20pass%20from%20the%20Aina.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYears%20later%2C%20in%20a%20cinematic%20twist%20of%20fate%2C%20while%20filming%20my%20second%20feature%20film%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaagh%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20a%20small%20village%20below%20Gulmarg%2C%20I%20bumped%20into%20Mohiuddin!%20Now%20in%20his%2070s%20with%20a%20white%20beard%20and%20missing%20teeth%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20tell%20him%20that%20I%20had%20not%20only%20met%20but%20also%20acted%20in%20a%20film%20with%20the%20great%20Amitabh%20Bachchan.%20But%20Mohiuddin%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20films%20anymore.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Mohiuddin%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20films%20anymore.%20It%20had%20been%20decades%20since%20he%20last%20watched%20a%20film.%20Providing%20for%20his%20family%20and%20survival%20had%20taken%20precedence.%20I%20invited%20him%20to%20be%20in%20front%20of%20the%20camera%20in%20a%20short%20scene%20in%20a%20bus.%20He%20hated%20it.%20The%20fact%20that%20it%20took%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20to%20can%20a%20couple%20of%20shots%20was%20too%20much%20for%20him.%20He%20politely%20took%20his%20leave%20as%20it%20was%20time%20for%20his%20evening%20prayer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165003%2FIMG_7469.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165003%2FIMG_7469.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165003%2FIMG_7469-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09165003%2FIMG_7469-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696392%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20author%2C%20Aamir%20Bashir%2C%20with%20Mohiuddin.%20Photo%3A%20Shanker%20Raman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20audience%20in%20Kashmir%20related%20to%20the%20Hindi%20films%20as%20a%20reference%20for%20the%20latest%20trends%20in%20fashion%20and%20music.%20Although%20a%20great%20number%20of%20films%20were%20shot%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20these%20were%20not%20about%20Kashmiri%20lives.%20Invariably%20the%20stories%20were%20about%20people%20from%20one%20of%20the%20big%20cities%20who%20were%20on%20vacation%20on%20a%20hill%20station%20or%20for%20song%20sequences.%20There%20were%20hardly%20any%20Kashmiri%20characters%2C%20other%20than%20the%20marginal%20shikarawala%20or%20a%20ghodawala.%20We%20could%20identify%20the%20locations%20instantly%E2%80%A6%20Pahalgam%2C%20Gulmarg%2C%20Sonamrag%2C%20Yusmarg%20and%20of%20course%20the%20Dal%20lake.%20In%20essence%2C%20Kashmiris%20were%20watching%20the%20fictional%20lives%20of%20tourists%20in%20their%20own%20backyard.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09171037%2FScreenshot-2024-02-09-at-4.57.19%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09171037%2FScreenshot-2024-02-09-at-4.57.19%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09171037%2FScreenshot-2024-02-09-at-4.57.19%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x163.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09171037%2FScreenshot-2024-02-09-at-4.57.19%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x557.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696404%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22653%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20the%20film%20%E2%80%98Junglee%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20early%201990%20militant%20groups%20ordered%20the%20closure%20of%20cinemas%20in%20Kashmir.%20They%20were%20soon%20taken%20over%20by%20paramilitary%20forces%20and%20some%2C%20like%20Firdaus%2C%20were%20even%20used%20as%20detention%20or%20interrogation%20centres.%20With%20the%20rising%20levels%20of%20violence%20and%20insecurity%2C%20films%20or%20entertainment%20was%20the%20last%20thing%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20minds.%20Getting%20home%20before%20dark%20became%20imperative.%20Soon%20Kashmir%20became%20a%20subject%20of%20interest%20for%20the%20Indian%20film%20industry%20rather%20than%20just%20a%20location%20for%20film%20shoots.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStarting%20with%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ERoja%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20films%20now%20had%20Kashmiri%20characters%20(still%20played%20by%20non-Kashmiri%20actors)%2C%20but%20they%20lacked%20nuance%20or%20agency.%20Young%20men%20misled%20by%20sinister%20anti-national%20elements%20from%20across%20the%20border%2C%20to%20be%20brought%20back%20into%20the%20mainstream%20by%20the%20Indian%20hero%2C%20or%20simply%20evil%20jihadists%20and%20corrupt%20opportunists%20who%20were%20to%20be%20vanquished%20by%20a%20man%20in%20uniform.%20The%20tourists%20now%20came%20on%20national%20security%20%2Fintelligence%20missions.%20The%20idyllic%20views%20were%20now%20foregrounded%20by%20vehicles%20being%20blown%20up%20and%20bullets%20whizzing%20around.%20A%20paradise%20with%20some%20locals%20who%20had%20gone%20astray%2C%20now%20needed%20saving%2C%20like%20a%20damsel%20in%20distress.%20All%20this%20while%20serenading%20or%20frolicking%20on%20the%20Dal%20lake%20or%20Mughal%20gardens%20because%2C%20hey%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20we%20roll.%20After%20the%20great%20silencing%20of%202019%20came%20the%20last%20word%20via%20a%20film%20backed%20by%20the%20state%2C%20which%20portrayed%20the%20entire%20Kashmiri%20Muslim%20population%20as%20terrorists%20responsible%20for%20the%20exodus%20of%20Kashmiri%20Pandits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkashmir-image-bollywood-article-370%5C%22%3EThrough%20the%20Lens%20of%20Bollywood%3A%20Kashmir%20as%20an%20Image%2C%20Kashmir%20as%20a%20Place%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20chasm%20between%20India%20and%20Kashmir%20shows%20up%20in%20Hindi%20cinema%20in%20sharp%20relief.%20Even%20though%20the%20films%20now%20had%20Kashmiri%20characters%2C%20they%20remained%20primarily%20about%20territory%20seen%20through%20the%20coloniser%E2%80%99s%20gaze.%20There%20was%20no%20room%20for%20any%20nuance%20or%20subtlety%2C%20and%20God%20forbid%20any%20discussion%20of%20political%20aspirations%20of%20the%20people%20without%20the%20prism%20of%20religious%20fanaticism%20and%20Islamophobia.%20Kashmiris%20however%2C%20still%20consume%20Bollywood%20films%20with%20great%20gusto.%20You%20will%20still%20hear%20songs%20from%20Hindi%20films%20at%20weddings%20or%20Instagram%20reels.%20Young%20men%20showing%20off%20their%20Salman%20leather%20jackets%20or%20Shahrukh%20haircuts.%20There%20is%20also%20the%20realisation%20that%20film%20shoots%20are%20good%20for%20the%20local%20economy.%20At%20the%20same%20time%20there%20is%20cynicism%20about%20the%20way%20they%20are%20represented%20in%20films%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20take%20the%20medium%20seriously.%20Fully%20aware%2C%20that%20when%20their%20representation%20in%20Indian%20news%20media%20could%20be%20spun%20and%20distorted%2C%20why%20would%20one%20expect%20to%20see%20realistic%20Kashmiri%20characters%20in%20films.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHaider%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20perhaps%20the%20only%20notable%20exception%20in%20a%20series%20of%20such%20mainstream%20films%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20memory%20keeps%20getting%20in%20the%20way%20of%20your%20history%E2%80%A6%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%A6%20If%20only%20somehow%20you%20could%20have%20been%20mine%2C%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ewhat%20would%20not%20have%20been%20possible%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20Agha%20Shahid%20Ali%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHaving%20survived%20in%20Mumbai%20as%20a%20reluctant%20actor%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20literally%20put%20my%20money%20where%20my%20mouth%20is%2C%20and%20wrote%20and%20directed%20my%20first%20film%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHarud%20(Autumn)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%202010.%20I%20did%20it%20partly%20to%20mitigate%20the%20frustrations%20I%20felt%20as%20an%20actor%2C%20but%20primarily%20to%20give%20voice%20and%20reclaim%20our%20own%20narrative%2C%20and%20in%20turn%20restore%20some%20dignity%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Kashmir.%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20beyond%20what%20one%20saw%20in%20the%20news%2C%20to%20explore%20the%20psychological%20state%20of%20a%20people%20living%20under%20violence%20and%20oppression%3Athe%20dysphoria%2C%20the%20disassociation%2C%20the%20humiliation%2C%20and%20the%20indignities%20suffered.%20And%20to%20do%20so%20in%20a%20manner%20far%20removed%20from%20the%20language%20and%20aesthetic%20of%20mainstream%20Indian%20cinema.%20The%20film%20went%20on%20to%20win%20the%20National%20Award%20for%20the%20best%20film%20in%20Urdu%20and%20was%20screened%20by%20Doordarshan%20several%20times.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20a%20scenario%20is%20unthinkable%20with%20my%20second%20feature%20film%2C%20released%20in%202022.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EMaagh%20(The%20Winter%20Within)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eis%20about%20resilience%20and%20the%20commitment%20women%20have%20towards%20the%20ideals%20of%20freedom%20and%20justice.%20Though%20it%20has%20won%20several%20awards%20at%20international%20film%20festivals%2C%20it%20has%20no%20takers%20in%20India.%20I%20see%20this%20as%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20shrinking%20space%20for%20any%20freedom%20of%20expression%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Kashmir%20and%20democracy%20at%20large%20in%20India.%20But%20Kashmiris%20will%20continue%20to%20draw%20sustenance%20by%20telling%20our%20stories%20for%20posterity%2C%20even%20if%20over%20kitchen%20fires%20%2C%20preparing%20an%20evening%20meal.%20in%20whispers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAamir%20Bashir%20is%20a%20filmmaker%20and%20actor.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707547545000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09170520%2F13191305844_0ef054e2b9_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkashmir-cinema-paradiso-past-present%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Before%20Kashmir%20was%20repression%20and%20violence%2C%20it%20was%20home%20for%20experiences%20and%20brushes%20with%20art.%20A%20filmmaker%20pens%20down%20some%20memories.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fkashmir-cinema-paradiso-past-present%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maharashtra%3A%20Despite%20Hate%20Speeches%2C%20Role%20in%20Violence%2C%20BJP's%20Vikram%20Pawaskar%20Goes%20Scot-Free%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10120937%2FEffect-2024-02-10T120918.846.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Between%20January%20and%20September%202023%2C%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leader%20Vikram%20Pawaskar%20was%20actively%20involved%20in%20delivering%20several%20hate%20speeches%20and%20flaring%20up%20communal%20tensions%20in%20the%20twin%20districts%20of%20Satara%20and%20Sangli%20in%20western%20Maharashtra.%20Electronic%20evidence%2C%20independent%20witnesses%2C%20and%20at%20least%20four%20FIRs%20point%20to%20his%20direct%20involvement%20in%20both%20public%20incitement%20of%20communal%20tension%20in%20the%20region%20and%20his%20conspiratorial%20role%20in%20the%20violent%20attack%20on%20a%20mosque%20in%20Satara%20district%20that%20claimed%20one%20life%20and%20serious%20injury%20to%20over%20a%20dozen.%20But%20for%20an%20entire%20year%2C%20the%20police%20have%20failed%20to%20initiate%20any%20kind%20of%20action%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Maharashtra%20police%20have%20failed%20in%20their%20duty%2C%20Shakir%20Islal%20Tamboli%2C%20a%2050-year-old%20rights-%20activist%20moved%20a%20writ%20petition%20before%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20last%20month.%20The%20elaborate%20petition%2C%20filed%20through%20his%20lawyer%20Lara%20Jesani%2C%20and%20represented%20by%20senior%20advocate%20Mihir%20Desai%2C%20chronicles%20events%20where%20Pawaskar%20had%20incited%20Hindu%20youth%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmaharashtra-satara-communal-violence%5C%22%3EPolice%20Say%20Peace%20Has%20Been%20Restored%20in%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20Satara%2C%20But%20Muslim%20Community%20Still%20in%20Fear%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20February%209%2C%20when%20the%20case%20came%20up%20for%20hearing%2C%20the%20public%20prosecutor%20Hiten%20Vengaonkar%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20before%20the%20court%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Satara%20police%20and%20once%20again%20issued%20a%20clean%20chit%20to%20Pawaskar.%20The%20affidavit%20was%20in%20response%20to%20the%20observations%20made%20by%20a%20division%20bench%20of%20justices%20Manjusha%20Deshpande%20and%20Revati%20Mohite%20Dere%20in%20the%20last%20hearing%20on%20January%2024.%20The%20judges%2C%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20charges%20levelled%20against%20the%20police%20and%20Pawaskar%2C%20had%20asked%20the%20police%20to%20tell%20the%20court%20why%20no%20action%20was%20initiated%20against%20Pawaskar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20on%20Friday%2C%20as%20the%20case%20came%20up%20for%20hearing%2C%20advocate%20Abhinav%20Chandrachud%20appeared%20before%20the%20court%20and%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20%E2%80%9Cintervene%E2%80%9D%20on%20behalf%20of%20Pawaskar.%20Since%20Abhinav%20Chandrachud%20had%20not%20filed%20an%20intervention%20application%2C%20the%20court%20didn%E2%80%99t%20grant%20him%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPawaskar%20is%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Maharashtra%20state%20vice%20president.%20Originally%20from%20Karad%20in%20Satara%20district%2C%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20Pawaskar%20has%20managed%20to%20gain%20control%20over%20the%20western%20Maharashtra%20region.%20Before%20him%2C%20it%20was%20another%20Hindutva%20leader%20Manohar%20alias%20Sambhaji%20Bhide%2C%20who%20was%20notorious%20for%20making%20communally%20charged%20statements%20in%20the%20region.%20Now%20as%20Bhide%2C%20who%20is%20close%20to%2090-%20year-old%2C%20has%20slowly%20phased%20out%20from%20public%20space%2C%20Pawaskar%20is%20being%20intentionally%20propped%20as%20the%20new%20Hindutva%20face%20of%20the%20region.%20Pawaskar%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Vinayak%20Pawaskar%2C%20is%20an%20established%20Hindutva%20leader%20in%20western%20Maharashtra%20and%20considered%20close%20to%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20Devendra%20Fadnavis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10121108%2F48364058_999024620282970_7467050065731780608_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22845%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10121108%2F48364058_999024620282970_7467050065731780608_n.jpg%20845w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10121108%2F48364058_999024620282970_7467050065731780608_n-298x300.jpg%20298w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10121108%2F48364058_999024620282970_7467050065731780608_n-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696481%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22852%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVikram%20Pawaskar%20(right).%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETamboli%2C%20who%20has%20been%20closely%20following%20Pawaskar%20and%20other%20disruptive%20Hindutva%20groups%20like%20Bhide%E2%80%99s%20Shiv%20Pratishthan%2C%20Hindu%20Janajagruti%20Samiti%20and%20Sanathan%20Sanstha%20in%20the%20region%2C%20says%20that%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20these%20organisations%20have%20been%20given%20a%20free%20pass%20to%20make%20inflammatory%20speeches%20and%20provoke%20people%20to%20directly%20attack%20the%20Muslim%20community.%20Each%20time%20these%20organisations%2C%20under%20an%20umbrella%20name%20Sakal%20Hindu%20Samaj%20organised%20events%20in%20the%20region%2C%20Tamboli%20intervened.%20Like%20days%20before%20the%20first%20speech%20delivered%20by%20Pawaskar%20on%20January%2024%2C%202023%2C%20Tamboli%20had%20notified%20the%20local%20police%20and%20their%20district%20representatives%20against%20the%20possible%20communal%20flare-ups%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20action%20and%20Pawaskar%2C%20as%20predicted%20by%20Tamboli%2C%20made%20insensitive%20and%20hate-filled%20statements%20against%20the%20Muslims.%20He%20openly%20called%20for%20a%20social%20boycott%20of%20the%20community%20and%20worse%2C%20threatened%20to%20harm%20children%20born%20to%20Muslim%20women.%20This%2C%20he%20claimed%2C%20was%20the%20only%20way%20to%20protect%20the%20%E2%80%9CHindu%20stree-%20dhan%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20patronising%20term%20coined%20by%20him%20to%20address%20Hindu%20women.%20Over%203%2C500%20people%20had%20attended%20Pawaskar%E2%80%99s%20public%20event%20and%20the%20video%20clips%20of%20his%20derogatory%20speech%20were%20widely%20circulated.%20In%20this%20particular%20incident%2C%20the%20FIR%20was%20filed%20only%20five%20months%20later%20in%20May%20following%20repeated%20letters%20to%20both%20the%20local%20and%20district%20police.%20However%2C%20no%20action%20was%20initiated%20against%20Pawaskar%20or%20other%20men%20involved%20in%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20high%20court%20questioned%20the%20prosecution%20for%20lack%20of%20action%20against%20Pawaskar%2C%20Vengaonkar%20had%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20police%20were%20waiting%20for%20a%20forensic%20report%20of%20the%20videography%20done%20at%20the%20event.%20The%20court%20had%20expressed%20surprise%20over%20the%20need%20for%20a%20forensic%20examination%20of%20the%20video%20that%20the%20police%20had%20themselves%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20another%20similar%20public%20event%20in%20June%2C%20Pawaskar%20made%20a%20similarly%20inciteful%20speech.%20Here%20too%2C%20the%20police%20filed%20an%20FIR%20but%20no%20action%20was%20taken.%20On%20September%2010%2C%20finally%2C%20a%20mosque%20was%20attacked%20in%20Pusesavali%20village%20and%2030-year-old%20Nurul%20Hasan%20Shikalgar%2C%20an%20engineer%20and%20a%20man%20who%20ran%20a%20local%20earthmover%2C%20was%20killed%20in%20the%20attack.%20Over%20a%20dozen%20other%20men%20suffered%20grievous%20injuries.%20In%20this%20incident%2C%20the%20police%20while%20arrested%20the%20attackers%2C%20the%20initial%20FIR%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20mention%20of%20criminal%20conspiracy%20that%20went%20into%20orchestrating%20the%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20after%20the%20media%20reports%20and%20consistent%20pressure%20from%20the%20Muslim%20community%20and%20rights%20activists%20like%20Tamboli%2C%20did%20the%20police%20finally%20enhance%20the%20sections.%20Section%20120%20(B)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20for%20criminal%20conspiracy%20was%20finally%20added%20and%20the%20complaint%20and%20other%20independent%20witnesses%20spoke%20of%20the%20conspiracy%20meeting%20that%20was%20organised%20at%20another%20person%20Sanghram%20Mali%E2%80%99s%20house.%20At%20least%20six%20independent%20witnesses%20have%20testified%20before%20a%20magistrate%20under%20section%20164%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETamboli%20says%20that%20the%20atmosphere%20was%20already%20vitiated%20in%20the%20region%20and%20many%20like%20him%20were%20ebing%20vigil.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20the%20moment%20I%20heard%20about%20this%20conspiracy%20meeting%2C%20I%20wrote%20to%20the%20Inspector%20General%20of%20Kolhapur%20Range%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tamboli%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20residents%20of%20Pusesavali%20village%20too%20met%20the%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20Sameer%20Shaikh%20and%20informed%20him%20about%20the%20threat%20they%20anticipated%20to%20their%20lives.%20Shaikh%20had%20accepted%20the%20letter%20but%20again%2C%20no%20action%20was%20taken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20Pusesavali%20incident%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20contacted%20a%20senior%20police%20official%20privy%20to%20the%20incident%2C%20who%2C%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20confirmed%20the%20letter.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmaharashtra-satara-communal-violence%5C%22%3Eofficer%20had%20claimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmen%20claimed%20that%20they%20had%20a%20threat%20to%20their%20lives%20from%20the%20Hindus%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20a%20generic%20statement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20that%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20violent%20attack%2C%20at%20least%20six%20witnesses%20including%20those%20who%20had%20overheard%20Pawaskar%20and%20others%20at%20the%20conspiracy%20meeting%20and%20those%20attacked%20at%20the%20mosque%20have%20given%20elaborate%20details%20of%20Pawaskar%E2%80%99s%20direct%20involvement.%20The%20police%20in%20the%20chargesheet%20too%20mention%20Pawaskar%2C%20yet%20haven%E2%80%99t%20made%20him%20an%20accused%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707547384000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10120937%2FEffect-2024-02-10T120918.846.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmaharashtra-despite-hate-speeches-role-in-violence-bjps-vikram-pawaskar-go-scot-free%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Electronic%20evidence%2C%20independent%20witnesses%2C%20and%20at%20least%20four%20FIRs%20point%20to%20the%20direct%20involvement%20of%20the%20BJP%20Maharashtra%20vice-president%20in%20public%20incitement%20of%20communal%20tension%20in%20the%20western%20Maharashtra%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmaharashtra-despite-hate-speeches-role-in-violence-bjps-vikram-pawaskar-go-scot-free%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Spain%E2%80%99s%20LGBT%20matador%3A%20'More%20will%20come%20out%20because%20of%20me'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707545271000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F185F%2Fproduction%2F_13259