67505%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsean-bell-what-the-military-shake-up-in-ukraine-means-for-the-war-13067505%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsean-bell-what-the-military-shake-up-in-ukraine-means-for-the-war-13067505%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2210-Year%20Jail%2C%20Rs%201%20Crore%20Fine%3A%20Anti-Cheating%20Law%20Comes%20Hard%20On%20Malpractices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20significant%20move%20to%20ensure%20fair%20play%20in%20competitive%20exams%2C%20Parliament%20passed%20a%20bill%20on%20Friday%20introducing%20strict%20penalties%20for%20malpractices.%20The%20Public%20Examinations%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Bill%2C%202024%2C%20allows%20for%20a%20maximum%20jail%20term%20of%2010%20years%20and%20a%20hefty%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20those%20found%20guilty%20of%20cheating%20or%20aiding%20in%20any%20form%20of%20irregularity.%20The%20bill%20sailed%20through%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20today%20with%20a%20voice%20vote%2C%20following%20its%20earlier%20approval%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20February%206th.%20Notably%2C%20amendments%20proposed%20by%20opposition%20members%20were%20rejected%20during%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20law%20sends%20a%20strong%20message%20against%20exam%20malpractices%2C%20aiming%20to%20level%20the%20playing%20field%20and%20ensure%20fair%20competition%20for%20all%20aspirants%20in%20crucial%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20aims%20to%20address%20dishonest%20actions%20and%20irregularities%20in%20competitive%20exams%20by%20imposing%20strict%20penalties.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20bill%20suggests%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20national%20technical%20committee%20on%20public%20examinations%20with%20the%20purpose%20of%20enhancing%20the%20security%20of%20computerized%20examination%20procedures.%20This%20committee%20will%20be%20responsible%20for%20providing%20rec